title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions,
blend in flour.	Remove from heat.
Beat in 1 cup of flour and add rest.	Add remaining ingredients and simmer covered for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and season squash and onion together.
Stir carrots, soup and sour cream into cooked mixture.
Melt margarine; put in dressing mix.
Add mixture to remaining ingredients.
Save some Pepperidge Farm mix for top.
Cook at 350° until done.
Makes 3 small casseroles.
Freezes good.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix all together except coconut. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle coconut on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheddar crisps *(from gourmet magazine)
directions: Cream butter and Cheddar until light and fluffy.
Continue beating and add flour a little at a time until combined.
Stir in dash of salt and cayenne.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Form into balls by heaping teaspoonfuls and place 2 inches apart on buttered baking sheets.
Flatten each with back of a floured fork.
Bake in middle of 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes approximately 55.
Freezes well.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Roux:
For 4 to 5-quarts gumbo, use 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup oil. Stir together in a heavy pan over medium-low heat until color of peanut butter.
Be careful not to burn.

title: great-grandma bednar's butter cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add soda into buttermilk and add to first mixture.
Add flour to make a soft cookie dough.
(Too much flour makes cookies too firm.)

Roll dough out on a lightly floured surface to approximately 1/3-inch thick and cut out your favorite cookie shapes with cookie cutters. Bake in a moderate oven (325° to 350°) until very lightly browned or about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies too brown causes them to be very hard and undesirable.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Mix in pumpkin, eggs and water.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.

title: german potato salad
directions: Steam potatoes and sausage together.
Cook bacon.
Add onions and drain.
Add celery and water to bacon.
Add vinegar and sugar; simmer 5 minutes more.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Combine with potatoes and sausage mixture.
Toss to coat.
Serve warm.

title: carrot salad with lemon dressing
directions: Place raisins and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat, cover, and let stand 15 minutes to absorb water.
Drain and place raisins, carrots, and celery in a medium bowl.
Place oil, lemon juice, salt, paprika, and mustard in a blender container.
Cover and blend.
Stir into salad, cover, and chill at least 6 hours.

title: cherry whip
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, powdered sugar and plain gelatin; press in long pan.
Beat Dream Whip with cold milk; add vanilla and sugar.
Add cream cheese.
Spread on top of graham cracker mixture.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Chill overnight.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: In shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Firmly press mixture across and up sides to form a shell. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in gravy mix, water and garlic salt; bring to a boil. Add mixed vegetables; reduce heat to medium and cook 5 minutes. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in potato shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: kay's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut and remove tops from peppers; scoop out seeds from inside of pepper.
In a large pan, place peppers, covering with water, and bring to a boil.
Cook them until semi-soft yet firm enough to fill.
In a large frying pan, combine beef, sliced onion, corn and stewed tomatoes with salt and pepper, cooking until beef is browned and vegetables are to boiling point, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
After mixture is thoroughly cooked through, take green peppers which have been drained on paper towel.
Place in small roasting pan or casserole dish which has been dotted with margarine or butter over bottom of pan.
Spoon in meat, corn and tomato mixture in each pepper.
Then top each pepper with bread crumbs; dot with butter or margarine and paprika.
Put in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Arrange over a plate of cooked rice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Separate eggs; add egg yolks and milk to dry mixture.
Mix well; add butter.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Add meringue if desired.

title: coffee bread
directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in 1/2 cup lukewarm milk.
In another bowl, mix remaining milk, sugar, salt, cardamon seed and a small amount of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add yeast and remaining flour, beating with a wooden spoon until smooth and firm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Roll into little balls and chill. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together over heat and dip balls in the chocolate mixture with a toothpick.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, melted oleo and crumbs to make crust. Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine softened oleo and powdered sugar and beat with mixer for 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Layer fruits in order.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with extra strawberries.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: kathy's sweet potato fluff
directions: Mix together and place in casserole dish.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until eggs are well mixed.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: bean sausage
directions: Mash the beans.
Mix them well with the bread cubes and egg. Add the seasoning
and moisten with milk. Shape the mixture in the form of sausage and roll in crumbs.
Brown in a little hot fat, turning to form a good crust all over.
Cook slowly, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put coconut and maraschino cherries on top.
Chill.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Take hamburger and make into patties. Salt and pepper to taste. Slice potatoes and onions. Put onions on top of patties. Then put slices of potatoes on top of onions. Put butter on potatoes. Bake at 375° to 400° for about an hour or until done in pan. Cover with aluminum foil.

title: bean dip
directions: Chop bacon fine and cook with onion.
Combine other ingredients and add to bacon mixture.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Then bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Add 1 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese to top of mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes. Serve with Fritos.

title: two cheese polenta
directions: In a bowl, stir together the cornmeal, 1 cup of cold water and salt.
In a medium saucepan, bring 3 cups of water to a boil. Over low heat, gradually stir in the cornmeal mixture and continue stirring until thickened.
Cover and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes.
Off heat, stir in Parmesan. Divide mixture evenly among three 12-ounce frozen juice concentrate cans.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: apples for fried pies
directions: *When using peaches do not peel.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix flour, mayo, milk and eggs well.
Add other ingredients. Sprinkle top with seafood seasonings. Cook at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: jackie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together brown sugar, white sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour and oatmeal.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake until light brown.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: For 1 gallon, cut tomatoes and let set overnight in salt water.
Put 1/2 gallon vinegar, sugar and pickling spices in pot. Bring to a boil.
Cut green and red peppers and onion.
Add to boiling mixture.
Squeeze tomatoes out of water and add to boiling mixture.
Let cook 3 hours.
Should be thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: party spinach balls(appetizer)
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture. Combine spinach with remaining ingredients, mixing well. Shape mixture into 3/4-inch balls and place on lightly greased (or spray with Pam) cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 11 dozen.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk in mixing bowl for 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add condensed milk and mix well.
Stir in bananas.
Layer vanilla wafers and pudding mixture in serving bowl, one-half at a time.
Chill for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: easy chili mac
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water (don't overcook); drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add Sloppy Joes sauce and chili powder. Stir in kidney beans and macaroni.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: First day:
Slice cucumbers lengthwise.
Soak in 2 gallons water and lime.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Combine whipping cream, vanilla, sugar and marshmallows.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows have melted.
Remove from heat; add coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread between split layers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Keep refrigerated.

title: kolocky cookies
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add flour.
Form in balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press to form hollow in center of ball.
Fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Sprinkle top with last three ingredients and cover tightly in a large glass salad bowl so that layers may be seen. Be sure that it is well covered with plastic wrap and well refrigerated. Serves 12.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt until warm, stirring constantly.
Add to a mixture of 2 1/2 cups flour and the yeast. Add eggs.
Beat at low speed 1/2 minute, scraping bowl; add potatoes and beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in by hand 2 1/2 cups flour.
Turn out on floured board.

title: super-duper potatoes
directions: Melt oleo and cheese with half and half.
Mix with potatoes. Pour in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
While baking, fry bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble bacon.
Add sour cream and bacon to potato mixture last 15 minutes of baking.

title: tuna stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks to bowl; mash with a fork.
Drain and finely flake tuna.
Combine with egg yolks.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pile mixture back into egg whites.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: lima bean-meat ball savory supper bake
directions: Place lima beans in a colander and run hot water over until they separate.
Drain and pour into a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine and mix thoroughly the ground beef, milk, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, chili powder and rosemary.
Shape into 2-inch balls and brown lightly in skillet in 5 tablespoons of melted shortening.
As beef balls brown, place in baking dish over beans.
Brown 2 cups of sliced onions in skillet.
Add tomato sauce and water and heat.
Pour over contents in baking dish.
Top with cubed Cheddar cheese and rings of green pepper.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix in saucepan butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and evaporated milk. Heat until melted.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast and let set while you heat milk to near boiling and then add sugar, butter, mashed potatoes and salt.
Let cool slightly before adding yeast mixture and 2 unbeaten eggs. Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Put into buttered bowl, cover and place in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 hours. When ready to bake, use only amount wanted or you can bake all (mixture will keep in refrigerator up to 1 week).
Shape into rolls of desired size.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen. Serve warm.

title: seven layer tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning and layer on bean dip.
Chop tomatoes and place over avocados. Dice onions and layer on tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over onion. Garnish with chile.

title: nicole's pasta and cheese
directions: Simmer browned beef, onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce and tomatoes for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: never fail yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add sugar and 1/2 cup flour. Cover and let stand in warm place until bubbly.
Add salt, eggs, shortening and remaining flour.
Let rise until double.
Roll out and cut.
Place in greased pan with sides touching.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mom's french toast
directions: Mix eggs and milk well; add cinnamon.
Cut bread into thick 1-inch slabs.
Dip bread into mix and allow to soak until saturated (about 30 seconds).
Fry in a large skillet in mix of oil and butter.
Eat plain, or with maple syrup, sprinkled with white or powdered sugar, or with more butter.

title: viennese chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Melt butter.
Cook onion, pepper, carrot and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in tomato, flour, paprika, salt and chicken stock; cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream, chicken and noodles. Turn into buttered 3-quart casserole and bake 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk cornbread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to hot (425°).
Lightly grease cornstick pan. Place in oven to warm while preparing batter.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a large bowl. Add eggs, buttermilk and butter; stir just to moisten.
Pour batter into each cornstick mold, filling each about 3/4 full. Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) for about 15 minutes or until tops are lightly browned.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 5 minutes. Using thin metal spatula, carefully remove sticks from pan. Repeat until all batter is used.
Makes about 28 cornbread sticks.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in fat.
Add to crumbled bread with salt, pepper and eggs.
Add broth to make a very soupy batter. Pour into baking pan and let set awhile.
Bake in 350° or higher oven.
Before putting dressing in oven, lay cooked pieces of chicken on top of dressing.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Boil beef for 2 minutes to remove salt.
Combine beef and other ingredients in blender until creamy.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with the buttermilk to the creamed mixture.
Add extracts.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, and raisins.
Make sauce by mixing mayo, sugar, and vinegar. Pour over mixture and let sit overnight. DO NOT stir.
Add bacon.
DO NOT mix until just before serving.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, berries and 2 tablespoons flour, tossing to coat fruit.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: white cloud
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then put cream cheese and sour cream and mix together. Then add powdered sugar. Then fold in the Cool Whip and grapes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. (Let them thaw in Jell-O mixture.)
Add pineapple, banana and nuts.
Chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a medium skillet, combine butter, brown sugar, milk and cinnamon. Cook over medium heat. Stir until smooth and bubbling. Add sweet potatoes until glazed.
Put in casserole dish. Cover with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In another bowl combine eggs, sour cream, milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir and mix well.
Fold in blueberries and cream cheese. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or an angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes, depending on pan.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage; crumble, drain and set aside.
Stir together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper until beaten well enough for scrambling.
Stir in jalapenos and sausage.
Spray skillet with Pam; cook just as you would scrambled eggs.
Lay flour tortilla flat; fill with a spoonful or two of egg mixture.
Add a spoonful of Cheddar cheese; roll up in tortilla shell.
These may be heated in microwave, one or two at a time, for a few seconds or until cheese melts.
Serve with salsa on top, if desired.
You may halve this recipe, if you wish.
Refrigerate leftovers in airtight container.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Mix first 4 items together, then add rhubarb.
Pour in 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
On top put butter and
cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: old time custard
directions: Mix for 3 minutes with an electric mixer.
Put in a 9-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°, then turn to 350° and bake for 30 minutes more until set.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Add milk.
Mix to a smooth dough.
Turn out on floured surface and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep, hot fat.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: green bean salad
directions: Pour this mixture over vegetables.
Let set overnight or longer before serving.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: fruit tea
directions: Steep tea for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags. Add sugar and stir well.
Mix frozen lemonade according to directions on the can and add to tea. Add the Hi-C juice and stir well.
Good either hot or cold.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 gallons.

title: crawfish fried rice
directions: Saute crawfish, onion and pepper in 2 to 3 tablespoons hot oil for 5 minutes.
Add rice and green peppers and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: *Small round cake decorations.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until blended.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Refrigerate.
Mix gelatin, pudding mix and water in medium saucepan until mixture just comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in fruit. Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with additional Cool Whip.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in three layers.

title: broccoli bacon salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Dice onion. Shred cheese.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble into small pieces.
Put all into large bowl.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar and pour over veggie mixture.
Toss thoroughly and serve.

title: italian spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels and milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add pecans.
Shape and drop by the teaspoon on waxed paper.
After hardened, dip in chocolate and wax melted in the top of a double boiler.

title: crispy easter nests
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and butter; mix until well blended.
Add noodles and plain M&M's; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Shape with greased fingers to form nests.
Let stand until firm.
Dust bottom of nests lightly with confectioners sugar if desired.
Fill with peanut M&M's before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 nests.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook
spaghetti
in
chicken
broth and bay leaf adding enough water
to keep it moist.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add
tomato sauce and cook slowly.
Add mushrooms, soup and deboned chicken, then simmer.
Add part of the cheese and
mix with spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender, remove bones; soak overnight in refrigerator in wine.
Chop chicken; mix any remaining wine with salad dressing.
Combine grapes with salad dressing.
Refrigerate. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a tube or Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes, or until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan; cool completely. Serve plain or with sweetened whipped cream.

title: frypan cookies
directions: Cook all ingredients (except Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut) for 10 minutes, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Butter hands (mixture will be hot).
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Layer in skillet onion, chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti.
Mix together cream soup and broth.
Pour over layers in skillet.
Cover and simmer until spaghetti is tender.
Don't stir.
When done, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese powder.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain pineapple. Blend all ingredients together. Do not add any juice or water. Garnish with additional cherries, if desired.

title: blueberry berry dessert
directions: Place berries and pineapple in a 9x13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the top and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: golden summer punch
directions: Add water to frozen concentrates as directed on cans.
Combine with apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Chill.
Serve in punch bowl.
Float block of ice in punch.
Garnish with orange slices. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: date pecan pie
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well.
Add pecans and dates.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: peachy orange cake
directions: Stir with spoon for 1 minute.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: felloine
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in butter or oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake covered 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Can be made a day ahead and stored in refrigerator.

title: blondie's refried beans
directions: Pour cooking oil in hot pan.
Drain beans. Put a spoonful at a time in pan.
Add a little bit of flour at a time and mash until desired consistency.

title: homemade scrapple
directions: Fry pork lightly.
(*If using sausage, after it is browned the grease should be discarded.)
Heat water to boiling in saucepan. Stir in cornmeal.
Add pork and seasoning and cook over low heat until very thick, stirring constantly.
Transfer to a 3 x 7-inch loaf pan and chill several hours or overnight.
Cover with wax paper to keep crust from forming.
Cut into thin slices and dip in flour and beaten egg and crumbs and fry in Crisco, about 2 tablespoons.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's holiday fruit salad
directions: In a small saucepan, mix and cook eggs, vinegar and sugar until thickened.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Combine all prepared fruit in a large bowl.
Fold in whipped cream and cooled egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: ginger and soy-glazed chicken
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Peel ginger and grate 1 tablespoon minced garlic.
Combine grated ginger, the garlic, soy sauce, sesame oil
and
vinegar.	Rub
chicken
cavity
with about 1 tablespoon of this mixture.
Slice remaining ginger and put in cavity.
Put chicken
on a rack in a roasting pan and bake 30 minutes.
Baste with ginger mixture.
Continue baking chicken, basting
every
15 minutes,
until
juices run clear when the inner
thigh
is pierced, about 45 minutes longer.
Stir-fried vegetables
and either rice or noodles complement the chicken well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and carrots in water 15 minutes; drain. Melt oleo and stir into stuffing.
Add enough water to moisten. Spread 1/2 stuffing in a greased 10-inch casserole.
Mix salad dressing, sour cream and soup into drained vegetables and mix lightly.
Put all on top of stuffing.
Add rest of stuffing on top of vegetables.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all; roll into balls.
Press with floured glass.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to first mixture.
Add milk alternately with flour and salt, which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla.
Lastly, fold in soda and vinegar.
Beat as for any other cake.
Mix per these instructions for velvet texture.
Pour into two (9-inch) pans which have been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and split, making four layers.
Ice with creamy white icing.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Thoroughly blend soda into persimmon pulp.
Add flour and rolled oats.
Blend.
Add salt, baking powder, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: angel food pudding cake
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Place in a single layer on bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cook pudding according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Pour pudding over cake and mix gently.
Spread pineapple over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip. Spread to edges.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Process chicken and vegetables through a food processor or grinder and mix together in a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and keep in refrigerator until ready to eat.
Take out what you need, add mayonnaise to mix together.
Great with crackers or on a sandwich.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: chipped ham sandwich filling
directions: Tear chipped ham in small pieces.
Pour remaining ingredients over and stir.
Bake in covered dish for 2 hours at 300°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
In another bowl, mix oil and water.
Pour over cheese mixture and blend.
Add other ingredients and cook in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake by recipe on box in sheet cake pan. Let cool.
Place in punch bowl in layers.

title: pear preserve rolls with poppy seed
directions: In mixing bowl stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and poppy seed.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, stirring just until moistened.
Knead on lightly floured surface for 8 to 10 strokes.
Roll into a 20 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread with softened butter, then with preserves.
Sprinkle with additional poppy seed.
Roll up, jelly-roll style, beginning with long side.
Seal edge. Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place cut side down in greased baking pan.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over rolls.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix in pistachio pudding mix, then Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Chill and serve.

title: manicotti
directions: Boil 8
noodles at a time for 6 minutes in water with 1 tablespoon oil and salt.
Brown meat and drain.
Combine bread and milk;
let
stand 2 minutes.
Add meat and other ingredients except
sauces
and Parmesan cheese.
Fill noodles.
Put half
of sauce
in casserole, add noodles, then rest of sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Remove from oven. While hot, punch holes in cake with straw. Pour onto hot cake the Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping. Let cool. Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with crushed Heath bar.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and remove skin if desired.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Add chicken and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes or longer.
Drain chicken from marinade, saving marinade. Place chicken on hot broiler rack or barbecue.
Broil chicken for 30 to 35 minutes or until cooked through, turning and basting with marinade 3 to 4 times during cooking.
Add onion rings from marinade during last 10 minutes of broiling time.
Serve chicken garnished with lemon wedges (optional).

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a heavy skillet and cook until all the liquid is dissolved, stirring constantly.
When liquid turns to sugar, pour on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Let cool and store in an airtight container.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla. Cook until thick, then add vanilla.
Beat the 2 egg whites.
Pour pudding mixture into a baked pie crust.
Add beaten egg whites.
Brown in moderate oven.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in canister until needed.
Use 1/3 cup in 1 cup boiling water.

title: pautie
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, pork and caraway seed.
Spoon mixture into pie crust. Place top crust on.
Cut slits in top crust. Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown crust.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onion in the butter over moderate low heat, stirring, until it is softened, stir in the ham, corned beef and the garlic; cook the mixture, stirring for 1 minute.
Stir in 6 tablespoons flour and cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring for 3 minutes.
Stir in the kraut, parsley, and broth; cook the mixture, stirring for 3 minutes or until it is thickened and pastelike.
Spread the mixture on a platter and chill it for 3 hours, or until it is cold.

title: caramel icing
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Set off heat.
Add vanilla and beat until right consistency to spread.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and all spices; mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top and fold/cut through batter (incorporate fairly well). Sprinkle nuts on top. Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Good warm or cold and also with whipped topping.

title: mary's strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.
Pour
in
freezer
and
finish filling with whole milk.
A few drops of red food coloring can be used to make a deeper
color
or use strawberry soda.
Fill to 3 inches of top of can.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1 cup warm water.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar, salt, butter and shortening in large bowl.
Add boiling water, stirring until butter and shortening melt.
Cool slightly.
Add dissolved yeast, stirring well.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour, beating at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: lasagna
directions: For meat sauce, in a frying pan, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add ground beef, onion and garlic powder.
Cook for about 18 minutes, or until browned.
In blender, place 1 can tomatoes; blend on high speed for 30 seconds, until finely chopped.
Add to beef mixture.
Stir in tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano and pepper; bring to a boil.
Set aside until needed.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix can of chili, can of Ro-Tel and 1 can water.
heat the Ro-Tel and chili in a pan.
Chop the onion and bell pepper.
Shred the cheese.
Grease a long casserole dish.
Place a tablespoon or more of meat in the middle of tortilla, then sprinkle some cheese, onion and pepper. Then roll it up.
Place seam side down in the pan.
Do all tortillas this way.
Then pour chili and Ro-Tel mixture on top.
Sprinkle more cheese and onion on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: philly onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Spread into 8-inch pie plate; cover. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve as a dip with Triscuits crackers.

title: ground beef taco casserole
directions: Toss potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and salt. Press in bottom and up the sides of baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp and artichokes
directions: Arrange artichoke hearts in baking dish (that has been sprayed with Pam).
Put shrimp over the artichokes.
Saute the mushrooms and put on top of the shrimp.
Make a thick cream sauce that the Worcestershire and sherry has been added to.
Put cream sauce over the top of the casserole.
Put Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cookie jar favorites
directions: Mix flour and baking soda (set aside).
Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and add vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture; add cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: shrimp fra diavolo(spicy shrimp)
directions: In a large skillet, saute shrimp and garlic in olive oil just until shrimp are pink and opaque.
(Do not overcook shrimp.)
Add grated lemon peel; set aside.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Dot casserole with 1/2 stick butter.
Line dish with 1/2 bag stuffing.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with the rest of the stuffing and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baby blue salad
directions: Toss greens with crumbled blue cheese and Balsamic Vinaigrette.
Arrange orange slices over greens; sprinkle with strawberries, and top with Sweet-and-Spicy pecans.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and yolks.
Mix dry ingredients, add to yolks, milk and sugar.
Add butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.

title: coleslaw
directions: Slice cabbage.
Combine all other ingredients; bring to boil. Pour over cabbage and toss.
This will stay crisp for several days.

title: tenderloin spinach salad
directions: Saute tenderloin in butter; add Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, green onions, mushrooms and parsley and add Parmesan cheese last.
Serve on bed of fresh spinach with Bleu cheese dressing on the side.
Also may be garnished with more cheese and black olives.

title: pickled corn salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix together in a bowl.
Mix liquid ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Let sit overnight before serving.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with celery sticks or cucumber slices.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper. Set aside. Cook the bacon. In a large casserole, pour in the baked beans. Add the rest of the ingredients. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours. Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: orange spiced carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine orange juice, brown sugar, cornstarch, ginger and nutmeg.
Blend well; stir in carrots.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press evenly against bottom and sides of well-greased spring-form pan.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over Crispix cereal.
Stir to coat evenly.
Place in brown paper bag with powdered sugar and shake well.
Serve in "new" dog dish.

title: lemon-pepper catfish
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and lemon-pepper and set aside. Beat eggs in another bowl and set aside. Dip filets in eggs and then in flour mixture until well coated; you may dip twice. Melt butter in a large skillet (electric skillets work great). Add 2 to 4 filets at a time. Cook, turning until brown on both sides.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix meat and macaroni and put in casserole.
Combine large can tomato sauce with water and seasonings.
Pour over mixture; put cheese on top. Add pepperoni slices and 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on English muffins. Cut into quarters. Place under broiler until heated.

title: baked dish
directions: Chop onions and dice celery.
Brown meat, onions and celery in tablespoon of shortening.
Mix with balance of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray an 8-inch square cake pan with vegetable oil spray.

title: spring omelet
directions: Saute asparagus in small amount of olive oil. Add eggs; scramble. Add shredded cheese and bacon bits just before removing from skillet.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients; by hand, stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 to 90 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; invert on cooling rack.
Cool completely.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix cinnamon in pie filling.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan 1/2 of batter. Spoon 1/2 apple pie filling over batter.
Repeat with remaining batter and pie filling.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil for 2 minutes the crushed berries and 1 cup water. Strain mixture, keeping liquid.
Add to liquid the sugar and cornstarch; boil.
Stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Add food coloring.
Place a small amount of mixture on pie crust. Fill crust with 1 1/2 cup berries and 1/2 of the liquid, then the remaining berries and finally the rest of the liquid.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: burlap bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Heat last 3 ingredients to 120° to 130°.
Add the liquid ingredients to 2 cups of the flour (margarine does not need to be melted).
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 30 minutes. Punch down.
Divide into 2 parts.
On lightly floured surface, roll or pat each half to a 14 x 7-inch rectangle.
Starting with short side, roll up tightly, pressing dough into roll with each turn. Pinch ends to seal.
Place in greased pan; let rise until double. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until loaves sound hollow when tapped.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in buttered pan; top with raisins and coconut.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour this over the bread cubes and raisins; if not moist enough, add more milk.
Bread should be nice and juicy.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: lazy woman's pickles
directions: Pack clean dry cucumbers in 1/2-gallon jar.
Fill with vinegar.
Add salt.
Let stand at least 6 weeks.
Slice and put a layer of cukes and a layer of sugar.
Can be left in vinegar as long as a year. Don't let vinegar go in the jar as you slice.
Use spices, if desired.

title: yogurt fruit pie
directions: Line bottom of baked pie shell with fresh fruit.
Beat in mixing bowl the yogurt, cottage cheese, honey and vanilla.

title: stroganoff to die for
directions: Cut meat into 1 or 2-inch cubes.
In a Ziploc bag, put flour, salt and pepper.
Put cubed meat in bag and shake.
Take meat from bag and place in skillet (electric) on 350° with 3 tablespoons oil.
Brown on all sides of meat.
Add onion to meat until the onion becomes transparent.
Cook for about 20 minutes on low heat. Add bell pepper and mushrooms; stir for a few minutes.
Add tomato soup and stir and let cook on simmer 30 minutes.

title: holiday cider
directions: Combine all ingredients except orange slices in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes. Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.
Float orange slices on top.

title: sliced cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and divide dough into thirds.
Leave one section of dough plain; shape into a long roll the diameter of a half dollar.
To 1/3 dough add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Shape into roll.
To other 1/3 you may add butterscotch chips, chopped nuts, dates, coconut, M&M's or anything the kids like.
Shape, chill and store in fridge.
Slice and bake as needed.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: banana boat
directions: Cut wedge section in banana.
Remove wedge.
Place marshmallows and chocolate chips in hollow in banana.
Cover marshmallow and chips with peeled back section of banana skin. Wrap in foil.
Place in coals until chocolate and marshmallow are heated.

title: baked whole cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and horseradish.
Frost cauliflower with mixture.
Place into baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place on serving dish.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt the chocolate bar and half the syrup over hot water. Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add chocolate mixture and the rest of the syrup.
Add the flour, buttermilk mixed with soda, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Take chicken off bones and cut into pieces. In large bowl, mix chicken, Ro-tel, soups, onion and green pepper. In 9

X 13 pan, put a layer of tortillas on bottom, then 1/2 chicken mixture and 1/2 the cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or in microwave on high for 20 minutes. Serve immediately. Top with Dorito chips, if desired.

title: screwball cake
directions: Sift together, in an ungreased baking pan, all dry ingredients. Make 3 holes in dry ingredient mixture.
In 1st hole add vinegar. In 2nd hole add vanilla.
In 3rd hole add oil.
Pour cold water over all and stir well.

title: cabbage tamales
directions: Mix thoroughly the meat and rice with the other ingredients (except cabbage leaves, water, shortening and catsup).
Soak cabbage leaves in hot water about 10 minutes.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown meat with onions and celery; drain fat.
Add soups.
Add a little milk if more moisture is desired.
Add mushrooms.

title: breaded baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except chicken and bread crumbs. Place chicken to coat and marinate in mixture overnight in refrigerator.

title: golden baked onions
directions: In a large skillet saute onions in margarine until tender (about 12 minutes).
In a bowl combine the soup, milk, pepper and 2 cups cheese.
Stir in onions.
Transfer to a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Brush bread slices with melted margarine on one side.
Arrange buttered side up over cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
If desired, broil 4 to 6 inches from heat until bread is golden brown. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion. Drain.
Add Prego sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes. Cook rotini noodles. Drain and add to sauce.
Put layer of 1/2 of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, then layer of pepperoni, layer of Mozzarella, layer of Cheddar and repeat layers.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in about a quart of hot water.
Cool and add juices and more sugar if desired.
Add ice cubes and ginger ale before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles in salt water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Cook chicken in salt water until tender.
Remove meat from bone and cut in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 quart casserole.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake in a 325° oven until hot.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix ingredients.
If batter is too thin, add a little more flour.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls in hot grease.
Drain on paper towel.

title: beef hot dish
directions: Brown onion, celery and green pepper in a little butter.
Add salted beef and brown.
Add soups and milk, blended with mayonnaise.
Cook noodles which have been chopped.
Place combined ingredients in a greased casserole and top with chopped cashews. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuit pizza
directions: Roll out biscuits on cookie sheet (individually).
Brown ground beef, drain grease.
Pour meat over biscuits.
Pour tomato sauce over meat, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomatoes and 1 quart water.
Add vegetables.
Cut into bite-size pieces; add water to cover vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Add 4 cubes of bouillon (beef).

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add almond extract.
Stir in peaches; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: teresa's mother's rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Mushrooms may be added.
Very good with chicken or beef.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Combine cake mix, pie filling, extract and eggs in a large bowl.
Pour into greased 10 x 15 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix these thoroughly and add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten the texture to a great height of Christian living.
Bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile.

title: 9 out of 10 times oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: sirloin tip roast
directions: Marinate roast in dressing overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325 degrees for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: country taters
directions: Mix
above
ingredients
well.
Cut
potatoes
in large strips and coat with mixture.
Place in a shallow pan and pour 1
stick melted margarine over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not peel potatoes.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: In an electric skillet, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Set heat at 280°.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into pieces.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: lunchtime gloop
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
Add Franco-American spaghetti and cook until heated through.
Do not drain hamburger or it won't be properly greasy.
Burn on pan if you want; that will only improve the flavor.
Serve with buttered Wonder bread.

title: frozen party salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Stir in fruit and sugar.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze.
Serves 10 to 13.

title: fruit roll
directions: Mix flour, shortening, milk and baking powder together and roll out thin.
Spread with fruit, roll and cut like cinnamon rolls.
Melt one stick oleo in pan and place cut rolls in pan. Boil together sugar and water, pour liquid over rolls.
Sugar can be sprinkled over top for glaze.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: tutti-frutti squares
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Press into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix all other ingredients and pour over crust.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar; set aside. Mix together eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Blend in flour mixture to the pumpkin mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into a well-greased cake pan. Bake about 1 hour at 350° (baking time will vary depending on size of pan).
Put cream cheese icing on cool cake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions in a big pot.
Drain excess fat.
Add water and taco mix.
Stir over medium heat while adding remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 45 minutes to an hour to blend flavors.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend flour, then oats with shortening mixture.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap into waxed paper.
Freeze and use as wanted.
Slice whole frozen. Bake 12 minutes or until browned at 400°.

title: cherry top cheese cake
directions: Mix well and press in tin.
Chill one hour.
(Can use ready made crust.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook in boiling, salted water until tender; cool.
Peel and grate coarsely.
Put soup and butter in a pan and heat it until the butter melts.
Add the other ingredients and add to the potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth top.

title: sheep dip
directions: Scoop out inside of bread.
Save top part of bread.
They should resemble a pot.
Mix cream cheese, sharp cheese, beef and onions.
Divide this mixture evenly and place inside of the bread. Place filled bread on a jellyroll pan.
The top portions of bread is used as a lid over the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash blueberries; drain on paper towels.

title: perfect meat loaf
directions: Mix meats thoroughly; add onion, celery and seasonings.
Soak bread cubes in milk; add eggs and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat with rotary beater.
Combine meat and egg mixture and form in loaf; place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Allow butter or margarine and cheese to soften, then cream together.
Add sugar and cream again.
To the mixture add 1 cup flour, then 3 eggs.
Stir well.
Add 1 cup flour, then 3 eggs. Stir well again.
Add remaining cup of flour and mix.
(You begin and end with flour.)
Add vanilla; stir well and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemony chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 8 x 11-inch baking dish. Stir together soup, sour cream and lemon juice. Pour over chicken. Crush Ritz crackers and mix with poppy seed. Sprinkle on top of soup mixture. Drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan with cooking spray.
Spread nuts and coconut in the pan. Mix cake mix as directed on package and pour over nuts and coconut.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients thoroughly and pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; bring to boil to soft ball stage (234°).
Add peanuts and oleo.
Then cook to hard crack stage (295°).
Then add salt.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Spread on large cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Makes about 4 pounds.

title: sugar bacon
directions: Lay out a sheet of wax paper.
Cover with brown sugar.
Batter both sides of bacon.
Lay out flat in an iron skillet.
Put oven at 350°.
Cook in skillet in the oven for 20 minutes.
When done, lay out flat on another piece of wax paper until cool.
Can cook eggs in drippings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Stir flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt together.
Beat butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Stir with flour mixture alternating with applesauce, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour, 10 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool to room temperature.
Spoon glaze made of confectioners sugar and apple juice over top of cake.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.

title: mountain lamb chops
directions: Combine olive oil, lemon juice, salt, oregano and pepper in large shallow baking dish.
Add lamb chops; turn to coat both sides with marinade.
Cover and marinate for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Melt Crisco in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Put chops in skillet.
Cook until meat is tender and browned.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Combine oatmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into 2 1/2-inch cookies.
Bake 11 minutes at 350°.

title: isabel's poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts; place in bottom of pan.
Mix soups and sour cream in pan.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers over this.
Melt margarine; drizzle this over crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: josie's sweet cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 40 minutes.

title: saucy carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and drain.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in mustard, salt and pepper.
Add carrots to sauce and heat.
Spoon into serving dish. Sprinkle with chives.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: apple tortillas
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and water in a saucepan and heat to dissolve sugar.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put about 1/4 cup apple pie filling onto each tortilla; roll.
Place seam side down in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour heated sugar mixture over tortillas.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn tortillas with seam side up. Bake another 20 minutes.
Serve with a dip of vanilla ice cream on top if desired.

title: tea punch
directions: Place sugar in 1
gallon container.
While tea is still hot, pour over sugar and mix
well.
Add juices and mix.
Fill container with enough water to
make
1 gallon.
(More or less sugar may be used depending upon your taste.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook steak strips and onion with oil until done and drain. Add seasoning sauce, soup, salt and pepper.
Stir until thick. Add sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: texas tumbleweed
directions: Melt chocolate; stir in nuts and shoestring potatoes. Mix thoroughly. Spread on wax paper. Refrigerate. When cooled, break into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into baking dish. Apply 1 cup crushed potato chips on top.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325°.

title: best ever chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; let stand for 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: buster's fish balls
directions: Combine fish, mashed potatoes, onions, eggs, salt and pepper. If mixture is too thick, add milk; if too thin, add flour.
Shape into balls or flat burgers.
Roll in flour and deep fat fry.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and shortening together. Then add buttermilk and water. Mix. Knead for 5 minutes. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Season with barbecue sauce to one's taste.
Put in casserole dish and top with bacon.
Bake at 325° until bacon is done.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, cloves and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and zucchini until sugar dissolves.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Pour in a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn on cake rack until cold.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, milk, sugar and salt together.
Pour over cabbage and stir well.
You may have to add more if you have a lot of cabbage.

title: party pizzas
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Brown ground chuck and drain.
Put both back in the skillet and add oregano, worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, and velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted. Spread onto party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and put in oven on broil until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Melt margarine with 1 cup sugar.
Quarter each biscuit.
Dip each one in the sugar/cinnamon mix.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour in greased iron skillet.
Bake until brown.

title: quick and easy tuna pot pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add carrots, onion and celery; saute until onion is translucent. Sprinkle vegetables with flour and stir quickly to combine.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and stir constantly, bringing to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add tuna and seasonings.
Stir to combine.
Remove from heat.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: With fork, mix together flour, 1/2 cup pecans and butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Options:
Ham instead of bacon.
Broccoli instead of spinach. Or egg, bacon and cheese for breakfast quiche.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except beef.
Mix well. Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour.
Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, meal, milk, soda, corn and drippings together and set aside.
Cook hamburger and onion together; drain.
Add cheese and peppers.
Grease and meal skillet.
Pour half bread mixture into skillet; add meat mixture and cover with rest of bread.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: molasses pull taffy
directions: Place the brown sugar, water, corn syrup, molasses and butter in a large saucepan; stir to blend and cook to 260° on a candy thermometer or to hard ball stage when tested in cold water. Flavor with vanilla or almond.
Pour onto buttered pan.
Cool. Pull, cut and wrap.

title: tuna zucchini slippers
directions: In skillet, saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add tomato, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add tuna and heat through. Cover zucchini with boiling salt water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix in heavy pan.
Beat eggs.
Add corn meal, salt, sugar and enough liquid to mix.
Mix, then add more liquid.
Cook in heavy pan for about 10 minutes or until thick.
Stir constantly.
Preheat oven 25 minutes at 400°.
Bake in greased pan.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all above; let stand 1 hour.
Pour in greased pan or casserole.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion powder and Worcestershire sauce and spread on a plate.
Drain crab meat and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Mix cocktail sauce and gelatine and spread on top of crab meat.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple trifle
directions: Bake cake mix by directions on box.
Cool cake and cut in small squares.
Set aside.
Drain pineapple tidbits and reserve juice.
Combine vanilla instant pudding mix, 1/2 cup of reserved pineapple juice, and milk in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with mixer, for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Fold in sour cream, and drained pineapple tidbits.
Place 1/3 of cake cubes in the bottom of a trifle bowl.
Drizzle with one to two tablespoons of remaining reserved pineapple juice.
Spoon in 1/3 of pudding mix. Repeat layers.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Just before serving spread top with cool whip.
Garnish if desired.
Yield 12 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine soups, water, mushrooms and margarine.
Heat.
Put rice in bottom of casserole and add all but 1 cup of soup mixture. Stir well.
Place chicken on top.
Pour remaining 1 cup of soup on top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 - 2 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine until soft.
Add sugar gradually; continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour gradually; fold in vanilla.
Roll dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a pecan half into each cookie. Bake for 18 minutes at 350°.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Beat the egg and add the milk and butter. Next, sift together and add the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill each 1/3 full.
Put into each hole the jelly.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat lightly and onion.
Place in pot; let come to boil and simmer until tender.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix melted cheese, mayonnaise and potatoes.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top, then bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: comstock apple pie filling
directions: Cook all ingredients (except apples) until mixture boils and looks slightly thick.
Peel and slice cooking apples into 7 (1-quart) jars; fill jars with cooked mixture.
Process in pressure cooker 15 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.
Each quart makes 1 deep-dish pie.

title: miles' fried chicken
directions: Mix with mortar and pestle the first 6 ingredients and add to 1 cup flour.
Dip chicken pieces in water, then flour and spice mixture.
Fry in hot oil about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a small saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients and stir over heat until melted.
Stir in onion and crab.
Heat, stirring occasionally, on medium heat until blended.
Reduce to low for holding.
Serve in a chafing dish with bland crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat next 4 items together; then add to eggs.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread pecan halves in unbaked pie crust. To the other mixture (eggs, syrup, etc.) add 3 tablespoons butter. Pour over pecans.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and 50 minutes at 300°.

title: polly simmons pound cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Add baking powder before you sift the third time.

In a large bowl, cream the butter, Crisco and salt. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add milk and flour mixture alternately. Add extract. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing cake from pan. Cake can be iced with your favorite icing or is delicious plain.

title: miniature quiches
directions: Divide pastry in half.
Roll out 1/2 at a time on a floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut 12 rounds from each half, using floured 3 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Line 3-inch muffin pan cups with rounds; set aside.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Fill paper cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese, egg, salt and sugar.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as directed.

title: fraselle
directions: Mix together the flour, oil, baking powder, pepper, salt and water.
Roll into long strips about 2 inches wide and cut into small slices on a slant.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for about 10 minutes on lower shelf, then 10 minutes on upper shelf until golden brown.

title: potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead dough.
Let rise.
Knead down and let rise again.
Grease 3 bread pans.
Knead dough; form into loaves and let rise in bread pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: mom's potato salad dressing
directions: Mix together and then boil until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in more canned milk until it is as thin as you want it.
Add some celery seed.

title: apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only or use muffin cups. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, apples and cinnamon. Mix well.
In separate bowl, blend apple juice, oil and egg.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 22 minutes. Makes 12.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 1 cup pineapple and blueberry juice, combined, to gelatin.
Stir in drained fruit and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate to congeal.

title: tortellini with veggies and chicken in cream sauce
directions: Saute veggies in large frypan.
Add cream, chicken and spices. Simmer over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Spoon sauce over cooked tortellini.
Top with bacon and Parmesan cheese.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 recipes for 20 or more people.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add other ingredients, except raisins and nuts.
Flour raisins and add with nuts to mixture.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: low-fat deliciously easy cake
directions: Select your favorite flavor of cake mix.
Spray desired size pan(s) with cooking spray.
Prepare according to package directions with the following modifications:
Add 1 tablespoon flour to cake mix and blend.
Substitute an equal amount of applesauce for vegetable oil and substitute an equal number of egg whites for whole eggs.
Cool in pan(s) on rack.
Remove when cool. Frost if desired.
Yields 16 servings.

title: fool-proof pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and whisk lightly. Cook on greased griddle or in greased skillet.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda.
In another bowl, combine butter, sugars, pudding and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts. Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: roll topped bean and hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in casserole dish.
Cut refrigerated biscuits in half and place pinwheel fashion on top.
Grate some cheese; sprinkle over top of all.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until rolls are not doughy.

title: cream pie
directions: Cook on top of stove until thickened.
Add 2 heaping teaspoons butter and vanilla flavoring.

title: green bean gourmet
directions: Mix well.
Save 2 tablespoons cracker crumbs for the top. Best to cover and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Use 2-inch deep baking dish for best results.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream.
Add to remainder of ingredients (except tortilla chips).
Bake at 350° 20-30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mother's night off
directions: Pare and slice potatoes.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. Slice onion on top of potatoes.
Place ground beef evenly over the top of potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: grandmother's chocolate picnic cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix baking soda and sour cream.
Add eggs, sour cream mixture and vanilla to butter and sugar.
Dissolve chocolate in hot water.
Add salt to flour.
Stir in flour mixture, alternating with chocolate.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: heaven on a plate chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, cornstarch and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy tuna bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/4 cup of onion rings.
Mix remaining onion rings, beans, tuna and chestnuts.
Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Fold into tuna mixture.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Garnish with reserved onion rings and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook macaroni shells and drain.
Put shells in casserole dish along with can of soup and 1/3 can of water.
Add can of tuna fish, sauteed bell pepper and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with Velveeta cheese.
Put in oven at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: grilled chicken with pasta
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in salad dressing for 1 to 4 hours. Grill 10 to 12 minutes on each side until tender and juice is clear.
Sprinkle with fresh ground pepper and cut into thin, short strips.
Serve over 1/2 cup hot linguini.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.
Each serving contains 229 calories, 24.5 g protein, 5 g fat, 66 mg chol. and 270 mg sodium.

title: rivel soup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients into crumbly stage.
Bring milk to boil.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture into boiling milk.
Continue to boil 2 minutes.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well with a fork.
Add margarine, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into two uncooked pie shells.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
I heat the oven to 425° and put the pies in. Turn back to 375°.
I think the hot oven sets the crust and filling.

title: bubble and squeak(traditional english dish)
directions: In large saucepan over high heat, in 2 inches boiling water, heat potatoes and cabbage to boiling.

Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender; drain. Meanwhile, in covered 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage links in 2 tablespoons water for 5 minutes.
Remove cover and brown sausages well on all sides.
Add potatoes, cabbage, salt and pepper to sausages; cook 5 minutes longer, occasionally turning sausages and vegetables with pancake turner.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: coconut tart pies
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
May substitute 9-inch pie shell with tart pie shells.

title: potato kugel
directions: Saute minced onion and butter/oleo lightly together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour or until edges are crisp. Makes six servings.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Measure flour, two cups sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice and baking powder into one bowl and mix well.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Peel and slice apples and sprinkle with combined cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar in a separate bowl.
Turn half of the butter into the prepared pan.
Cover with half of the prepared apples.
Spread the rest of batter over top, then rest of apples. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with a fork.
Cool and turn on a platter.

title: pineapple bake
directions: In bowl, mix eggs, milk and pineapple with juice and bread cubes.
In second bowl, cream the margarine and sugar.
When creamy, add egg mixture.
Put in oblong dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spread over bottom of pan.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over other ingredients.
Pat down.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: hearts of romaine and radish salad(alfresco summer dinner with leslie and bob e.)
directions: Whisk together lemon zest, lemon juice, white wine vinegar and salt and pepper to taste; then whisk in olive oil until emulsified. Tear enough romaine into bite-sized pieces to measure about 8 cups. Cut radishes into julienne strips.
Toss romaine and radishes with lemon vinaigrette.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Ranch mix and chicken. Chill. Roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into thin strips.
Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steak, mushrooms and onion; saute 10 minutes or until steak is browned and vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat; drain and pat dry with paper towels.

title: mazie buzzard's salmon loaf
directions: Season to taste with salt and pepper; mix.
Pour into Pyrex loaf pan.
Bake one hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
I serve with a light white sauce.

title: chewy coconut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add raisins.
Mix well.
Add soda and salt to flour; add to creamed mixture.
Then add the oatmeal and last, the coconut. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. If they are overbaked, they will be hard instead of chewy.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of each pepper.
Remove seeds.
Cover peppers in boiling, salt water and cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook beef, onion and garlic in skillet over medium heat; stir to crumble meat.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs, and stir well.
Stuff peppers with beef mixture. Place in shallow baking dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beefy rice casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion and pepper.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish (13 x 9-inch). Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and is lightly browned.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix and knead 10 or
more times on floured surface.
Pat out and cut.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in muffin tins at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 16 cupcake size muffins.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Add butter, flour, egg yolks and other ingredients to mashed eggplant after it cools.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a pan of water.

title: mariachi drumsticks(a crispy chicken appetizer with mexican flair)
directions: In large resealable plastic bag, combine chips and taco spices and seasonings.
Dampen chicken with water and shake off excess. Place a few pieces at a time in plastic bag; shake thoroughly to coat with chips.

title: christmas puffs
directions: Cream butter with powdered sugar until light.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla; gradually sift in flour and salt, blending well to make a stiff dough.
Form into small balls (teaspoon is just right).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
With a wooden spoon, make a well in center of cookie.
Beat egg white until foamy in small bowl.
Fold in sugar until meringue stands in stiff peaks. Fold in pecans; spoon into wells.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top each cookie with half a cherry.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: egg casserole(this is a good brunch or supper dish)
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with the crescent rolls, pushing together the edges to form a solid crust for bottom. Mix eggs (5 to 8), one for each person, and 1 for pot.
Mix with milk, salt and pepper (like scrambled egg mixture) and pour over bread.

title: pete's meat balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together meat.
Blend in bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and oil.
Add all remaining ingredients and combine well.
Roll into meat balls.
Bake in oven for 12 minutes or until done.
Serve with Pete's famous sauce!
(Recipe can be doubled, tripled, etc.) Serving size:
4 adults.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Grate orange peel and squeeze juice from oranges.
Add enough water to orange juice to make 1 cup.
Beat cake mix (dry), 1 tablespoon orange peel, juice, oil and eggs in a large bowl on low speed (30 seconds).
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat the cream cheese, reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberry halves and kiwi slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yummy-tummy banana cake
directions: Mash bananas or beat in mixer. Add all remaining ingredients; blend on low speed. Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Heat oven to 350°. Bake 60 to 70 minutes or for a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: yellow squasherole
directions: Place 2 tablespoons oleo in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave on High about 1 minute until melted.
Add crumbs and pecans. Microwave 2 minutes; stir after 1 minute.
Pour crumbs onto wax paper and set aside.

title: ma styrk's pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat granulated sugar, lemon juice and pumpkin.
Fold into pumpkin mixture flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and ginger.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 2-inch cookie sheet.
Pour in batter and top with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on powdered tea towel.
Roll up and cool 1/2 hour.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: raisin, oatmeal, apple muffins
directions: Beat egg. Stir in all remaining ingredients, stirring just until blended. Pour batter into 12 lightly greased muffin tins. Fill tins 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done. Makes 12 muffins.

title: easy-cheesy appetizer
directions: Put Ritz crackers on a cookie sheet (as many as you want to serve).
Put a marshmallow on top of each Ritz cracker.
Top all with a slice of your favorite sharp cheese (about an inch by an inch piece).
Broil in oven, watching, until cheese starts to melt.
Don't burn the roof of your mouth.
