Serve while warm.

title: c-sharp seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: beet jelly
directions: Wash beets; boil to make juice.
Mix in Pectin and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar; return to boil.
Boil hard 4 to 6 minutes; seal in jars.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Cook sausage.
Saute onions in oil.
Add rice to onions.
Add well beaten eggs and soy sauce to this and then add sausage.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add mushrooms, soups, sauces, seasonings and flour.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: grandma's old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well.
Add ginger, cinnamon oil, eggs and cooking oil.
Mix until all lumps are gone.
Add milk slowly; add flour, mixing with hands or dough hooks.
Place the cup of flour in a large bowl and lightly knead dough therein.
Pat dough into cakes 3 to 4 inches long, or roll thin and cut into gingerbread men.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° for about 8 minutes until lightly browned.
Beat egg whites with sugar and brush tops and bottoms before they cool.
Serve hot with a cold glass of milk.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and oleo.
Put in 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: all-purpose herb butter
directions: Mix butter and herbs.
Store in refrigerator for about one month and in the freezer for about three.

title: coy's cheesy chicken
directions: Combine the rice, mushrooms, onion, salt, pepper and mushroom soup.
Put in greased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Press chicken breasts into mixture.
Cover with Cheddar soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and pistachio pudding into Cool Whip. Add marshmallows and pecans (can leave pecans off).

title: banana cake
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix with mixer.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Unfold crescent rolls and place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish to form a crust.
Sprinkle sausage on top of crust and cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Pour over top of cheese.
(Add salt and pepper to taste to eggs.)
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Divide popcorn into 2 greased 9 x 13 pans. Boil sugar, syrup and margarine for 5 minutes after it comes to a rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add soda. Stir well and while still foaming, pour over popcorn. Mix until coated. Bake 1 hour at 250°. Stir about every 15 minutes to separate popcorn.

title: pizza dough
directions: Measure water into bowl.
Add sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Sprinkle yeast over water and let stand 10 minutes. Stir well.
Add oil, salt and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Turn dough out on floured board and knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Gather dough into a round.
Put in a greased bowl; cover with a damp cloth and let rise in a warm place until it more than doubles, about 2 hours.
Punch down.
Divide dough into 2 equal pieces and roll and stretch each piece to fit a 14-inch pizza pan.
If dough is very bouncy, let it rest a few minutes until it will roll more easily.
If dough isn't quite the right size when you get in the pan, press and stretch it until you can seal it firmly to the sides of the pan.
If you don't have pizza pans, roll the dough into 14-inch rounds and put them on large cookie sheets; roll edges under a little to hold the filling. Top the crust with filling and bake at 450°.
Bake immediately.
No more rising.

title: easy salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces, leaving the peeling on them.
Cut up cucumbers first; pour enough vinegar over them to cover them.
Cut up onions next, then the peppers.
Slightly salt each layer.
Cut up tomatoes last and sprinkle with sugar.
Let set in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.
Do not mix until ready to serve.

title: macaroni goulash
directions: Fry hamburger meat with onion.
Pour off grease.
Cook macaroni as directed; drain.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, corn oil, and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and nuts.
Combine with zucchini mixture.
Put in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool before turning out.
Cream cheese icing is great on this.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cook
on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients except lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce to boiling in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; heat until hot.
Makes about 2 cups sauce; 25 calories per tablespoon.

title: sunshine golden yellow cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, then add the 3/4 cup milk and the Crisco. Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed on electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla. Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into two greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit filled meringue shells
directions: Place egg whites in a small mixing bowl and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cover a baking sheet with plain, brown paper.
Draw six 3-inch circles on the paper.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate meat overnight.
Excellent for beef roast.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Put deskinned chicken breasts (4 to 6) in the bottom of a glass oven pan.

title: chicken and chilies casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, light cream, onion, chilies, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, chicken and 2 cups of the cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Leftover meat of any kind may be substituted for chicken.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Heat soups, milk and butter.
Add rice.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Brush chicken with melted butter. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: nutty million dollar fudge
directions: Mix marshmallows, chocolate chips, nuts, oleo or butter and vanilla in a large bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar and evaporated milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for exactly twelve minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over marshmallow mixture; stir until well mixed.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill at least twenty-four hours.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: aunt sue's cheese wafers
directions: Mix well.
Shape in rolls; refrigerate.
Slice thinly (1/4-inch).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(Or use Kraft extra sharp Cheddar and add more flour.)

title: caramel apple squares
directions: Can use 2 cans of pie filling if you want more apples in it.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high for 11 hours.
Add 1/2 cup white cooking wine.
Cook for 1 hour longer.
Add oil of cinnamon to taste.
Put in glass jars to seal.
Makes 3 quarts of apple butter.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Add vanilla, apples and pecans. Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mary's best lemon pie
directions: Sift together 1 cup of the sugar and the cream of tartar. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly fold in sugar mixture and beat until well blended.
Butter the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Scrape the meringue mixture into the pie plate, building it up around the edges to fashion a shell.
Place in a preheated 275° oven and bake 1 hour.
Remove and place on rack to cool.

title: combination vegetable dish
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions.
Add broccoli when beans are partially cooked.
Cook until beans and broccoli are tender.
Drain.
Saute water chestnuts in butter for 5 minutes.
Add to vegetables and toss lightly.
Serve.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat all the ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cake is done. As soon as it is done, remove from oven and turn it out onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle more powdered sugar onto top of cake and roll up (cake and towel together).
Let cool.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese with remaining ingredients, except tortillas. Spread mixture on tortillas; roll up jelly roll style.
Slice into 1-inch pieces; secure with toothpicks.
Serve with salsa.

title: dirt cake
directions: The idea behind this
dessert is to make it look like a potted plant you
can eat!
Grind Oreos in blender; set aside. Mix pudding, milk,
powdered
sugar
and
Cool	Whip, blending together.
Cream margarine	and cream cheese together.
Add to pudding mixture.
Line a flower planter with foil.	Layer some cookies
on
bottom,
then
some
pudding	mixture.
Continue alternating layers, ending	with cookie layer on top.
Stick a plastic or silk or fresh flower arrangement on top.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll in flour.
Place in well-greased dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together with leftover flour.
Sprinkle over the top of the meat.
Add 1 cup water.
Place foil over baking dish. Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: irene's pound cake
directions: Mix thoroughly together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Slowly add flour.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Blend cottage cheese and 2 sticks margarine.
Sift in flour; blend until dough forms a ball (may be done in food processor). Divide dough into fourths.
If dough seems too soft to handle, refrigerate until firm enough to roll out.
On floured cloth, roll one quarter into a circle about 10 to 12 inches in diameter.
Brush with melted margarine; sprinkle with cinnamon, 1/4 of nuts and brown sugar.
Cut circle into 16 wedges.
Starting with wide end of each piece, roll up like crescent rolls.
Mix egg yolk with water; brush on each cookie.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 400°.
Repeat with each section of dough.
While still warm, drizzle with confectioners sugar glaze, if desired.
Makes 64 cookies.

title: best cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and quarter medium cucumbers.
Soak in ice or real cold water for about 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and pack in quart jars.
To each quart, add 3 stalks of celery and 3 slices of onion.
Boil the vinegar, sugar and salt together for about 5 to 10 minutes. Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook cheese and milk together in double boiler until smooth. Add seasonings and macaroni.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Bake in moderate 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until done. Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 17 g, fat 17 g, calories 274.
One serving = 2 meat high fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; add hash browns.
Place diced onions on top.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream together and spread over potatoes.
Spread cheese over everything.
Melt butter and mix with corn flakes.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix as on box.
Makes 3 layers.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Melt butter in 3-quart kettle until golden brown.
Add carrots and onions.
Cover and cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk.
Add half of potatoes, mash rest of them and add with remaining ingredients.
Heat until steaming hot.

title: stump hole cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, nuts and oleo.
Press into greased 13
x 9-inch pan.

title: darlene's special burritos
directions: Brown ground beef with seasonings.
Add onion and jalapenos and simmer until onion is transparent.
Meanwhile, peel and grate potatoes.
Add potatoes to meat mixture.
Mix well and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat tortillas in oven or microwave for 2 minutes.
Place several tablespoons of meat mixture in center of tortilla.
Fold edges up envelope fashion and secure with a wooden toothpick.
Burritos should be square when folded. Place burrito carefully into hot oil in large skillet until golden brown on both sides and crispy.
Place on paper towels to drain. Serve hot with salsa!

title: tomatoes stuffed with egg salad
directions: Combine eggs, celery, olives and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Scoop out centers of tomatoes and fill with egg salad.
Top with additional olive slices and chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Wesson oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda. Mix cocoa and food coloring.
Add vinegar.

title: kool-aid jelly
directions: Mix water and Kool-Aid.
Add Sure-Jell.
Cook to boil and add sugar.
Cook at rolling boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Sprinkle the chicken pieces with seasoned salt and cayenne pepper to taste. In gallon storage bag, put the flour and chicken pieces. Shake well and store in the refrigerator, shaking to keep coated. May have to use more flour.

title: franklin cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of flour to coat cherries, pineapple and nuts before adding to the batter.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well, bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: savory cheese, tomato and onion pie
directions: Prepare pastry; line a 10-inch pie dish and chill.
Grate all the cheese; toss it with the flour.
Melt the butter in a large skillet.
Slice onions; saute them very gently in butter until they begin to turn golden, about 1/2 hour.
Spread about 1/3 of cheese over bottom of pie dish.
Spread the onions over it.
In butter that is left in pan, heat tomato slices with chopped basil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Arrange tomato slices over the onions.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Beat eggs with cream; pour mixture over the cheese.
If you like nutmeg, sprinkle a little on the top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes, or until the top browns nicely.
Serve hot in wedges.
Serves 6.

title: super soup
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Add tomatoes, bouillon cube and water; simmer.
Just before serving, top hot soup with Mozzarella cheese.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients but hash browns and potato chips. Blend together until smooth. Fold in thawed potatoes.
Pour into greased baking dish (either 3-quart or 10 x 13-inch glass pan). Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until slightly browned and bubbly.

title: veggie salad
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mocha custard
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°. Put the boiling water in your blender container and drop in the chocolate. Let it sit for 5 minutes or so. Add the coffee crystals, heavy cream, eggs, Splenda and salt and blend for a minute or so. Spray a 1-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray and pour the mixture into it. (If you prefer, pour into individual custard cups.) Place the casserole or custard cups in a larger pan filled with hot water and place the entire thing in the oven. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool, then chill well before serving. (The chilling makes a big difference in the texture.) Yield: 4 generous servings.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers, carrots and celery very fine. Put in bowl and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours.
Goes good with meats.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring all liquid items to a boil.
Do not overcook.
Mixture is ready when drops from spoon look thicker.
When sugar is dissolved, add baking soda.
Pop the corn (optional, add nuts). While mixture is hot, pour over popped popcorn.

title: chow mein sub gum
directions: Sprinkle ginger on meat.
Sprinkle garlic powder, salt and pepper on vegetables.
Thicken chicken bouillon and water with cornstarch.
Serve over rice, noodles or soy sauce.
Serves 12.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Beat
cream
cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a
time,
mixing well after each addition.
Combine	2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup flour with cranberries and nuts. Fold
into	batter.
Batter
will be very thick.
Spoon into 10-inch
Bundt
pan,
greased.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or	until
done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan. Cool.
Before serving dust with powdered sugar.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix.
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches over beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans; add 2 quarts water and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar
and
water.
Cool.
Add strawberries, banana and pineapple.
Fold in whipped sour cream.
Chill sour cream before whipping.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add banana, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Stir in soda and flour.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: infallible rice
directions: Serves 4 hungry or 6 polite people.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: You will need paper cups.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place chicken into the baking dish in a single layer.
Sprinkle Italian dressing mix over chicken.
One packet will cover 4 to 6 breasts. No other seasoning is needed.
Place one thin pat of butter in the center of each breast.
Bake until done, about 30 minutes (depending on the size of the chicken breast).

title: aunt marcie's chili
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic salt and then combine all ingredients.
Simmer until ready.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Set aside.
In separate larger bowl, mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry mixture and mix thoroughly. Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Fill blender about 2/3 full of crushed ice.
Add about 1 1/2 cups of apple juice.
Blend until smooth.
Add banana, apple, frozen strawberries and sweetener.	Blend all together to make a frozen drink.
Serves 2-4.

title: clam pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make sure to include the clam juice from both cans of clams.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add oil; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat in carrots. Add pineapple and pecans.
Bake at 325°.

title: crab dip
directions: In a small bowl mix cream cheese and crab meat.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over unmolded cream cheese mixture.
Chill for 1 hour and serve with crackers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients; cut in shortening. Combine milk and egg; add to mixture just until all is moistened. Add berries and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put in casserole and cover with 20 crushed crackers which have been mixed with 1 stick of melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix orange jello and 1 can crushed pineapple.
Heat until jello dissolves.
Add cream cheese; stir until it melts.
Add apricots.
Let it set until it starts to gel.
Fold in Cool Whip and the nuts.

title: onion burgers
directions: In large bowl, combine onion soup mix, water and ground beef. Shape into 8 patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Makes
8 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Will also need a 1 gallon jug.

title: favorite refrigerator bread(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven 400 degrees. Mix together water, sugar and salt. Crumble yeast into mixture. Stir until dissolved.
Then add eggs and shortening.
Mix in first by spoon and then by hand, mashed potatoes.
Knead until smooth.

title: better than love cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Simmer pineapple and sugar until syrupy.
Spoon evenly over cake including liquid. Let set overnight.
Cook vanilla pudding according to directions. Pour over cake when cool.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut to taste.
Add chopped pecans and maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican meatballs
directions: Mix together the ground beef, eggs, half of the onion, 2/3 of the garlic, coriander and salt. Shape the mixture into 2-inch balls.

title: streusel cream peach pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Arrange peaches in pastry. Sprinkle sugar and nutmeg over peaches.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and margarine at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and egg until well combined.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each in sugar, place on greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Add eggs.
Stir in corn, milk and salt.
Melt margarine in lightly greased 2-quart baking dish; pour in corn mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for one hour or until firm.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Place sugar in heavy saucepan.
Add water and cream of tartar. Bring to a boil without stirring.
Cook until syrup reaches 240° on candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and continue beating until almost stiff.
Still beating, add sugar mixture in fine stream.
It is important to add sugar mixture slowly.
Keep beating at high
speed until thick.
Frosts 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and powder.
Add broccoli and shredded carrots.
Heat to boiling, stirring well.
Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add cooked spaghetti; heat through and serve hot.

title: swedish tea cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat 1/2 cup powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix together flour, almonds and salt until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set but not brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slivered almonds may be added as an option.

title: soup and c. j. moody's cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes or less.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in loaf or layer pan 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken captain
directions: Saute parsley, peppers and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes, mace, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add raisins and chicken.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Serve over rice with almonds on top.

title: chinese chow mein
directions: Slice celery crosswise.
Chop onion and saute in a small amount of vegetable oil.
Brown ground meat with onion and celery. Add mixed vegetables and water chestnuts.
Season with soy sauce. Serve over cooked rice with noodles on top.
Soy sauce may be added to individual's taste.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: In a buttered casserole, mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until bubbling.

title: shipwreck beans
directions: Cook bacon crisp, cool, crumble and set aside.
Brown beef and drain.
Add cut up onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine ketchup and brown sugar; stir into beef mixture.
Stir in pork and beans and bacon except for 2 tablespoons.
Put mixture into 8 or 9-inch baking dish; top with remaining bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar and salt. Cut in 3/4 cup butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until light brown.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in a skillet.
Put cooked rice in a large pot with chopped tomatoes.
Add beef, pepper and onion mixture; mix thoroughly.
Add tomato juice and cook on top of stove on medium heat until done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O and stir.
Whip in cranberry sauce.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in sour cream and nuts.
Chill in a Jell-O mold container.
Beautiful and delicious.
Great at Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: raw potato cakes
directions: Combine ingredients, adding enough flour to hold together. Fry in shortening (drop by tablespoon).

title: brown caramel
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups sugar, Crisco, margarine, Karo, salt and milk in	large
saucepan.
Stir until dissolved over low heat. Place 1/2 cup
sugar
in heavy pan and stir it until it browns and turns to	syrup.	Add 3/4 cup water to syrup and stir.
It will lump, but keep
on
low heat until it all dissolves.
Add to first mixture and
cook
until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add vanilla, cool and beat well.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
Coat wok or skillet well with cooking spray.
Allow to heat at medium high for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add chicken and soy sauce; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove chicken, reserving the pan drippings.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add onions and green pepper to wok; stir-fry 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Return chicken to wok.
Stir in water chestnuts and mushrooms.

title: momzy's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Add soup, cheese, pimiento, chicken, salt and pepper.
Blend well. Sprinkle with garlic salt and simmer 30 minutes. Serve over spaghetti, macaroni or rice.

title: smoked sausage(macaroni and cheese casserole))
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Slice sausage and broccoli into 1/2-inch pieces and mix with macaroni and cheese, then add soup.
Mix thoroughly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Add red pepper to taste (optional).

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown beef lightly in skillet without any added fat, stirring frequently.
Add pork and beans, tomatoes and salt.
Grease a baking dish.
Pour half the mixture in.
Cover with slices of onion.
Add remaining meat-bean mixture.
Top with strips of bacon and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix first four ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish or pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Mix remainder of the ingredients in bowl and spread on top of the partially baked crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool; cut in pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in bowl.
Beat eggs in another bowl and add cherries and juice from cherries, cooking oil, diced apples and nuts to eggs.
Mix well with dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: nilla fruit pie
directions: Finely crush 37 Nilla wafers.
In bowl, combine crumbs with margarine; press onto bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate.
Make pie filling according to package directions for pie using milk. Stand remaining 13 wafers around side of pie plate, pressing firmly against crust.
Spread filling into prepared crust.
Before serving, arrange fruit slices on top of pie.
Serves 8.

title: superb doughnuts
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to shortening.
Mix alternately with milk. Dough will be very soft.
To avoid sticking, rub flour thoroughly with heavy canvas cloth.
Turn dough onto cloth, then fold the four corners, one at a time, over the soft dough to lightly coat with flour.
With as little handling as possible, roll dough 3/4-inch thick.
After rolling, let stand 15 minutes before cutting to make doughnuts easier to handle (this is important). Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch or 3-inch doughnut cutter.
Fry until brown in hot fat (375°), turning when first crack appears (turn with spoon handle to avoid piercing doughnuts).
Takes about 1 1/2 minutes for total frying of doughnuts.
Drain on absorbent paper. Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip ice cream cake
directions: In large bowl, put softened ice cream, crushed cookies and Cool Whip.
Mix all together well.
Pour into cake pan with lid or foil on it and put into freezer until frozen.
Can be made ahead of time.
Makes a good dessert for drop in company.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meat and drain off the fat; place in a large baking dish. Add the beans and season with brown sugar, catsup, mustard and vinegar or lemon juice so it is like a barbecue sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sift together the flour, 1 cup of the sugar, salt and baking powder.
Blend in the milk. Pour the mixture into the dish.
Toss the peaches with the remaining sugar and the cinnamon, then spread them on top of the crust mixture.
Bake in preheated oven until the crust rises and turns golden, about 1 hour.
Serve warm with the whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saut onion, celery and bell pepper. Add sausage and cook until sausage is done. Drain well. Add all other ingredients, mixing well. Grate Cheddar cheese over top. Microwave, uncovered, for approximately 10 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on crackers with garnish of a slice of green olive or carrot.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Baste a couple of times.

title: quickie casserole
directions: Mix together in a casserole and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and Karo syrup in a large saucepan and cook until sugar melts.
Add marshmallows.
Cook until turns into soft ball when dropped into cold water.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, then add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: grandma lewis' velvet salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Before cutting fruit, dry with a clean cloth.
Scald the pineapple juice in double boiler.
Stir in yolks of well beaten eggs.
When cold, add whipped cream.
Mix with fruit and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: apple lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add pineapple, apple and nuts.
Mix together cottage cheese, salad dressing and cream.
Add this to gelatin mixture.
Let set in refrigerator.
Apples will come to the top.

title: mrs. gertrude weaver's hot or cold salad dressing
directions: Mix the
first	4
ingredients good, then add the water and vinegar.
Stir in a little butter while cooking.

title: parsley and wheat salad (middle eastern)(tabooleh)
directions: Combine ingredients in deep bowl.
Toss together and serve with crisp romaine lettuce leaves or tender grape leaves.
If you want to be creative add a cucumber, chopped fine, or any garden vegetable to your own liking.
Delicious with Syrian bread.
Make a pita sandwich!

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Measure oatmeal then put into blender until it turns into powder.
Mix with flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all ingredients and add chocolate chips.
Grate 8 ounce chocolate bar and add to mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Make golf ball sized cookies.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: sweetheart fantasy fudge(makes 3 pounds)
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 238°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in 3 quart pot. Saute garlic and onion until transparent. Add basil and continue sauteing for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce and continue cooking for 2 to 3 minutes. Cut up tomatoes and add. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook on simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in soda.

title: chicken noodle soupgroves, texas
directions: Get soup out of cabinet and open with can opener.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots, drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into well-greased round cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Layer asparagus in dish.
Sprinkle chopped olives.
Sprinkle 1/2 package stuffing mix.
Pour melted Cheez Whiz over layers.
Melt margarine and pour on top.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: sour cream chocolate mint cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Alternate sour cream and flour to first mixture.
Add nuts and mint chips.
Chill dough. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
For a change, divide dough in half and add 1/2 cup coconut.

title: white chili
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, over medium heat, saute in oil the onion and garlic.
Add seasonings (cumin, coriander and oregano).
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, add beans, corn, onion garlic mixture and the cubed chicken. Add bouillon and cheese. Cover and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Before starting, put oats and peanut butter in separate cups. Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil for 1 minute.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: mom's caramel rolls
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough.
Roll out, cover with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as jellyroll, slice.
Butter bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix caramel sauce: sugar, margarine and ice cream. Melt together and mix until creamy.
Put in bottom of pan and place rolls on top, brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best rich brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Beat eggs and salt.
Add sugar; fold in chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and flour.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Simple and delicious.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix in bowl and bake at 350° in casserole dish about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Add vanilla, squash and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: six-cup salad
directions: Drain all fruits; mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight.
Serve on lettuce.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Catch one rabbit.
Careful or he'll run on you.
Clean, wash and cut in quarters.
Put him in a jar of salty water.
Put the lid on tight and refrigerate.
Soak overnight while you sleep late. Next morning, heat deep skillet hot with grease.
It takes a lot. Brown rabbit that has been rolled in flour.
This should take about an hour.
Cover with water; turn the heat down to simmer, then let it cook until it's real, real tender.
Keep covered with water; don't let it boil dry.
That's the only way for rabbit to fry. Talk about good!
Chicken just isn't on it.
I prefer a rabbit in skillet.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Blend ingredients together and pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and cut into cubes.

title: hard tack
directions: Mix sugar, karo and water in saucepan. Place over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Cook without stirring until mixture forms a hard ball.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto a greased sheet.
After it hardens, cut with scissors or break into pieces.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in a large warm mixing bowl the Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine sugar and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook sugar mixture to soft ball stage or until candy thermometer registers 235°.
Pour over the peanut butter mixture. Stir until mixed.
Spread in a buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan. Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Combine flour and soda.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Add 1 cup of flour, then 1/2 cup of sour cream, another cup of flour, remainder of cream, 1/2 cup of flour (dredge pecans and raisins in other half), vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake in four layers in 300° oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes, boil in
about 1 quart water, add margarine to boiling water.
Mix
eggs
and flour (depending on how many rivvels you like).
Add
this
to
potatoes, simmer until potatoes and rivvels are
cooked.
Salt
and
pepper to taste. If mixture is too thick
it
can
be
thinned
with water.
If mixture is too thin, add some flour.
It should be creamy.

title: quick tomato aspic
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Heat tomato juice to boil and add to soaked gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and chill until firm.

title: minnie mouse's cookie recipe
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour and salt.
Mix with butter, egg, sugar and vanilla mixture.
Chill dough 3 hours.
(Preheat oven to 350°.)
On floured, covered surface roll out the dough to 1/8-inch in thickness.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 minutes.

title: carnation 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, then cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add nuts, marshmallows, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat vigorously 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Top with whole or chopped nuts, if desired.

title: german chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Ice with Coconut Filling.

title: shortcake
directions: Beat together and put in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: poppy seed bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix ingredients 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° (top should crack and toothpick inserted into center should come out clean).
Cool 10 minutes.
Poke holes and pour glaze over bread.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Blend all ingredients about 20 seconds; beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: 1 meal dish
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and add onions (cook some).
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients to pot. Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 9 hours.

title: caramel coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Add coconut and 1/2 cup pecans. Cook until golden, stirring frequently. Set mixture aside and cool slightly. Combine cream cheese and condensed milk and beat at medium speed until smooth. Fold in topping. Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pastry shell. Drizzle 1/4 caramel over each pie. Repeat layers with remaining cream cheese mixture, caramel topping, and coconut mixture. Cover and freeze pies for at least 8 hours. Let frozen pies stand at room temperature for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and freeze in Dixie cups. Remove from cups and add Seven-Up.
Mix thoroughly.
Enjoy!

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses, then dry ingredients.
Allow to stand in refrigerator for 2 days, to allow spice to go through.
Roll out on floured board; cut with fancy Christmas cutters.
Bake on cookie sheets in hot oven until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
Place in airtight cans until ready to serve.
Yields several hundred.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles as directed on box.
Rinse and set aside.
Brown ground beef, add spaghetti sauce and warm over low heat and set aside.

In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan spread about 1 cup sauce, then layer lasagna noodles, cottage cheese, noodles, 1 cup sauce, noodles, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese, noodles, mushrooms, noodles, sauce and rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Best to let set for about 15 minutes.

title: wanda's hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix and let set for 5 minutes.
Roll about 1 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pan.
Allow space between biscuits to rise and spread out.
Bake
at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Recipe may be halved.
Whole recipe makes a lot of biscuits.

title: honey dew candy
directions: Stir continuously until it forms soft ball, 235° on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla.
Beat until it begins to cream.
Add pecans and pour into a buttered dish.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cook eggs until hard-cooked.
Adding Heinz vinegar to water prior to cooking keeps eggs from cracking during cooking.
It will be easier to remove the shells afterwards.
Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash thoroughly, using hand mixer.
Add remaining ingredients while continuing to mix.
Refill whites with mixture, using egg pastry bag or a spoon.
Makes 48 deviled eggs.

title: king ranch hamburger casserole
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with corn chips. Brown hamburger meat and add all ingredients.
Pour over chips and sprinkle with chili powder.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Butter pizza pan.
Spread cookie dough on pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread over cool cookie.
Top with whatever fruits you desire.
Spread strawberry glaze over all.
(If using fresh peaches, peach pie glaze can be used.)
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cream the cream cheese; blend in 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread over cooled pretzels. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, breaking them up with a fork as you stir.
Chill until slightly thickened. Pour over Cool Whip layer.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry sherbet(definitely for spring!)
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar and let stand until juicy (about 1 1/2 hours).
Mash or puree in blender; strain seeds (optional). Add milk, orange juice and cinnamon; mix well.
Freeze in crank-type freezer or pour mixture into freezer trays or loaf pans and freeze about 3 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Pack in plastic containers for freezer.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: mrs. will johnson's bell pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions, sprinkle with salt and cover with boiling water.
Let stand until cool; drain.
Place in a boiler and add vinegar and sugar.
Boil 20 minutes and seal in jars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn,
beans and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients except
crackers
and
margarine.
Crush
crackers and sprinkle on top.
Pour melted margarine over and bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 25 minutes.

title: chicken rose
directions: Cut chicken
breasts in half and remove skin.
Trim all visible
fat.
Place
chicken in 1 1/2 quart casserole sprayed with
Pam.	Combine remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.	Serve over rice with juices.

title: mexican diet dip(this one is just because it's awful good.)
directions: The last 2 items can be to taste.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large glass bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen peas and broccoli separately.
Drain.
Heat together mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over vegetables in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, mix well with a fork, flour, sugar and salt; add shortening and mix with flour mixture until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions and shape into a flat circle.
Wrap each in waxed paper and chill 1/2 hour. Lightly flour both sides of pie patties.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface.
May be kept in refrigerator for 3 days.

title: cheesy corn bread
directions: Sift salt, flour, corn meal and baking powder together. Combine with remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake in greased 8 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°; insert cornbread and reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: torta primavera
directions: Basic Crepe Batter:
Make crepes ahead and refrigerate (24 hours, if possible).

title: easy double decker fudge
directions: Microwave Directions:
Line 9-inch square pan or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil; lightly butter foil.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, place peanut butter chips, 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk and butter.

In second medium microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips and remaining sweetened condensed milk. Microwave bowl with peanut butter chips at High 1 minute or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred; stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Immediately pour and spread evenly into prepared pan.
Microwave bowl with chocolate chips at High 1 minute or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth; stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Immediately pour and spread over peanut butter layer; cool.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: pork chop and fried rice
directions: Mix soups together in a bowl.
Add 1 soup can of water.
Stir together.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of soup to use later.
Mix rice and seasoning in bowl with remaining soup.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chops on rice/soup mixture and pour reserved 1 1/2 cups soup over chops.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes more to brown top.

title: chicken pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over high flame.
Add chicken; stir-fry until pieces turn white.
Add green peppers, onion, cumin and cayenne. Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add additional oil, if necessary.
Stir in drained pasta, corn and salt.
Cover; cook 2 minutes.
Drain tomatoes with chilies, reserving liquid.
Add tomatoes with chilies to cooked mixture.
Mix cornstarch with half of the reserved liquid.
Add to wok; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover; heat 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: almost candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix together all except potato chips and eggs and place in casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips and egg slices.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: potato-tomato soup
directions: Wash, peel and cut potatoes into small chunks.
Put in a large pot and add enough water to cover tops of potatoes.
Bring to a boil and cook until soft.
Add oil, then salt and pepper to taste. Last, add tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. Let's eat!
Great on a cold day!

title: lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and Parmesan cheese in bowl. Cook noodles and add to cheese mixture.
Pour cooked meat sauce into baking dish, cover with cheese and noodle mixture.
Cover with slices of Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german sour cream peach pie
directions: Place peach halves tightly together in unbaked crust.
Beat eggs; add sugar and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Dust with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 375° and bake 35 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or 2 (9-inch) pans or a tube pan.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and chocolate; mix until blended.
Sift flour with soda and salt.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients.
In a separate bowl combine the bread, warm milk, eggs and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with meat mixture.
Place in loaf pan.
Brush steak sauce on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat, drain and set aside.
In large heavy pot, put tomatoes.
Mash tomatoes into pieces.
Add chili hot beans, chili mix and ground meat.
Fill pot rest of the way with water. Stir good.
Bring to a boil then down to simmer for about 2 hours. Add more water during this time if needed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tijuana casserole
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given in an oblong casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Place chopped bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce, mushrooms, basil and oregano together. In casserole dish, cover bottom of dish lightly with olive oil. Spread some of the sauce on bottom of dish, then place 4 of the patties on the bottom. Spread some sauce on patties, then put some of the cheese (both) on top of the sauce, then repeat again, patties, sauce and cheese. Place in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix like pie dough.
Divide dough in half and roll half to size of jelly roll pan, 15 x 10-inch.
Cover bottom of crust with corn flakes or Total or Kellogg's 19 (crushed).
Then cover with 4 cups sliced apples (or more) and sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll other crust and place on top.
Pinch side edges together.
Prick top with fork.
Beat egg whites until frothy and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then drizzle powdered sugar frosting over top.
Serve warm.

title: "a happy home"
directions: Cream together friendship and tenderness.
Very lightly beat in a bowl of loyalty and a cup of faith, hope and charity.
Be sure to add a spoonful of gaiety that sings and also the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with the sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan and serve repeatedly.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Combine mushroom soup and celery soup in crock-pot.
Heat on low.
Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides in shortening in saucepan.
Remove roast to plate.
Stir onion soup mix into drippings in saucepan.
Cook until brown.
Add 1 soup can water; mix well.
Add to soups in crock-pot; mix well.
Add roast.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: smooth chocolate frosting
directions: Combine powdered sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Stir in melted chocolate and butter.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Frost tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: tender round steak
directions: Brown and season round steak, then put in casserole dish with 1 cup water.
Cover tightly and bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 250° or 300° until meat is tender to cut with a fork.
(The water also makes the gravy.)

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; place on medium heat.
Stir until butter and sugar are melted and dissolved. Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Quickly add peanut butter, oats, vanilla and coconut or nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: flowerpot dessert
directions: Cream together the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add pudding, Cool Whip and milk.
Mix until thick.
Set aside. Grind the Oreos until fine (should look like dirt).
In a new, clean flowerpot, starting with cookies, alternate pudding mix to layer.
Make sure you end with ground cookies.
You can put gummy worms into dirt mix and serve with a spade to have even more fun.

title: thick hamburger soup
directions: Place meat in a 4-quart casserole.
Microwave 5 minutes on High (100%), stirring twice.
Add remaining ingredients and cover. Microwave on High (100%), or simmer on stove 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 30 minutes before serving.

title: tuna boats
directions: Combine all ingredients and stuff mixture into celery stalks. Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Cut into 2-inch lengths to serve.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: Bring pineapple, jello and sugar to a boil.
Cook until thick. Have whipping cream or evaporated milk chilled to whip.
Whip until stiff.
Add to chilled pineapple mixture and beat with mixer until well blended.
Place in a graham cracker pie crust and chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine in a soup pot over low heat.

Add onion, carrot and garlic. Cook, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender and wilted. Crush tomatoes in their liquid and add to the pot along with the chicken broth, potato, basil, nutmeg and salt. Cook, covered, over low heat for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Let cool to room temperature. Puree in a blender, in small batches, adding a bit of milk to each batch. Return to soup pot and adjust seasonings. Before serving, warm through over very low heat. Do not boil. Serves 6.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Slice potatoes (raw) in dish like scalloped potatoes.
Cover with
a pork chop for each serving.
Cover with sliced onion. Slice another layer of potatoes on top.
Pour 1 can of diced or stewed tomatoes over all.
Salt and pepper.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: easy frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and powdered sugar. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Divide into 2 crusts and freeze. Can be served with chocolate sauce and chopped nuts, if wanted. Take out of freezer about 45 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Add rice, seasonings and 1/4 cup tomatoes to hamburger.
Stuff green peppers loosely and place in covered dish, pouring remaining 1 cup tomatoes over, cook 1 hour at 350°.
May add a little water, if necessary.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower(conventional or microwave)
directions: Cook cauliflower in water for 5 minutes or until tender (in microwave, cook 8 to 9 minutes on High).
Put in casserole.
Mix mayonnaise, onion and mustard.
Pour over cauliflower.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (in microwave, 1 1/2 minutes on Low).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken. Add tomatoes and soup.
Simmer 20 minutes. Layer tortillas, chicken and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream with milk. Mix until creamy. Mix other ingredients into mix. Stir well. Chill until ready to serve.

title: chili con carne with beans
directions: Saute onion, garlic and peppers in oil.
Add beef and brown. Add the remaining ingredients (except water).
Cover and simmer over low flame for 1 hour.
Add water, if needed.

title: one pan dinner
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breast and flour.
In large flat oven grill pan, spread aluminum foil long enough to tent over all vegetables.
Place chicken at one end of pan.
Open beans and corn, drain, then dump separately in pan.
Place potatoes in pan next.
Spread onions over green beans.
Pour melted margarine over all ingredients, but make sure the chicken is coated with it. Tent foil over vegetables and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini(for 50)
directions: Mix together chicken, pimento and parsley.
Add salt and cooking oil to boiling water, along with spaghetti, and cook according to directions.
Drain.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown
meat
in
a
pot; drain oil out.
Add water; let boil with
ginger
until meat is soft.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions;
cook
for	15
minutes.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and stew tomatoes; cook to boil, then add celery last.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small, bite-size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Add the sugar to the mayonnaise and spread over the top as you would frosting.
Top with the grated cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.
At serving time, garnish with additional bacon and parsley.

title: portuguese sweet bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in milk, 3/4 cup sugar, salt, 3 eggs, the margarine and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix together right before serving.
You can freeze fruit in an ice ring for punch if desired.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix juice with cheese, then add dry ingredients and freeze in serving bowl.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Roast turkey at 350°.
Will be done when corn pops and blows the "a--" off the turkey!

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and mix until creamy in color.
Add dried beef, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Roll into ball and then roll into nuts.
Chill.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and soda and set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and both sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla; gradually stir in flour mixture.
Add candy and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until cookies are brown.

title: lasagna with white sauce
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef and onion until meat is brown; drain. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bouillon and seasonings.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then stir in sugar until dissolved.
Allow to cool slightly and add cold water, lemon concentrate, pineapple juice and 7-Up.
Pour into large container and freeze.
Pull out of freezer a few hours to thaw before using.

title: hearty vegetable seafood chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion, garlic and peppers; saute until tender.
Remove skin and bones from fish; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Add to pan.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring gently, until fish is opaque.
Add crushed tomatoes and all canning liquids, frozen mixed vegetables, bay leaf and seasonings.
(Shrimp may be added at this point, if desired.)
Reduce heat, cover pan and cook until vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes.

title: snow-top chocolate cookies
directions: Beat margarine with electric mixer on medium for about 30 seconds or until softened.
Gradually beat in powdered sugar, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat and stir in flour and milk. Shape a well-rounded teaspoon of dough around each Kiss.
Place cookies pointed side up onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Remove cookies and cool on wire racks.
Frost peaks of cookies with fluffy frosting.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cream; bring to rolling boil. Reduce heat; for 5 minutes cook.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stir until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Stir, then add marshmallow cream.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into 13x9 inch pan that has been greased with butter or margarine. Let cool. When cold, cut into squares.

title: roll mix(plain or sweet)
directions: Mix shortening, hot water and sugar and set aside.
Mix yeast, warm
water,
flour,
salt
and
eggs.
Mix everything together. Roll and cut.
Set aside for 2 hours (plain rolls). Bake at 375° until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Quickly add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir until mixed real well.
Drop by
teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or cookie sheet.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and Creole seasoning. In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and add mayonnaise mixture. Toss gently and chill. Serves 8.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Combine salad
oil, lemon juice, water, onions, garlic, pepper, salt, rosemary leaves, oregano, thyme and celery salt. Marinate cubed beef
overnight
in
covered dish.
Place meat, cherry tomatoes, bell
peppers and fresh mushrooms on skewers. Grill until done.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes.
Strain and serve hot in mugs or cups. Yield: 12 servings.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into wedges and chop onion.
Place both in a small amount of water and steam until squash is soft and onion clear. Strain.
Take a potato masher and mash out excess water.
Take a 2-quart casserole dish and layer squash.
Season with salt and pepper and some crushed crackers.
Pour some melted butter over layer and repeat until gone.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: fresh orange pound cake
directions: Grate rind of 1 orange.
Use 1/2 of rind in cake batter and save other half for icing.
Squeeze out juice of 1 orange and use half of juice in cake batter and other half in icing.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except chicken and blend until sugar dissolves.
Add chicken and marinate at least 30 minutes, turning halfway through.
Remove from marinade and grill over hot coals for 25 minutes or until done.
Baste with sauce to keep from drying out, but do not save sauce for future use.
Can be served alone or on a bun.
Delicious served alone or on a bun.

title: green potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes.
Boil in salted water until almost tender; drain and dry over heat.
Combine spinach and parsley and steam 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain and add them to the potatoes.

title: punch
directions: Color any color you wish.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Mix soy sauce, garlic and oil together.
Pour over cut up steak in heavy skillet.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Brown meat, pepper, onion and celery; season to taste.
Cover, cook on low 20 minutes; stir until thickened.
Add soup, water and cut up tomatoes.
Cover and cook 30 minutes on low.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Mix together.
Pat into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool very slightly.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until sugar is dissolved.
Then mix all other ingredients with it.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: southern sweet potato pones
directions: Grate peeled potato with fine grater.
Measure and combine with next 6 ingredients.
Add to well-beaten egg and blend.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.

title: salt risen bread
directions: We remember our mother, Mrs. Charlie Ayers, making Salt Risen Bread from a recipe that we never saw written down but heard it from her and observed her making the bread many, many times.
It was such a favorite with the family that some of the Ayers grandchildren still ask if anybody in the family remembers how to make it.
That Salt Risen Bread, just out of the oven, dripping with real butter, was indeed delectable to the Ayers family and who ever happened to be visiting at the time.

title: dulce de leche
directions: Pour milk into saucepan.
Add several drops of lemon juice. Cook over low heat until curdling occurs.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Continue to cook over low heat.
(Milk will continue to curdle and get thicker.)
Add sugar.
Continue to simmer until mixture is moist, but not soupy.
Cooking time:
Approximately 3 to 4 hours.

title: lefse
directions: Boil potatoes and put through ricer or mash fine.
Add margarine, cream and salt; mix well.
Cool overnight.
Next morning, put through ricer again.
Mix half of the potato mixture with 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour.
Form into balls.
Roll very thin. Bake on grill until small brown spots appear.
Turn and bake. Cover with towel to keep soft, then continue with other half of mixture.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together by hand all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry whip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and eat.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour and pepper in dish.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture to coat.
Shake off excess.

title: mud ball fudge candy
directions: Stir and place on heat.
Do not stir while cooking.
Cook until forms a firm soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat. Add chunk of butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until can roll into balls.
Add nuts if desired.

title: cherry yummy
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and sugar; press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate or bake.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Make Dream Whip according to directions.
Mix stiff.
Add to cream cheese.
Pour into crust.
Top with pie filling.

title: fr. bob's hot chili
directions: Brown the meat in the corn oil and drain.
Put the meat and all the other ingredients except for the beans into a large soup pot; bring to a boil and then reduce heat and simmer for an hour, stirring occasionally.
Add the beans and simmer for 15 more minutes.
Serve with cornbread and a mixed salad.
(One can also add some grated Cheddar cheese to the chili.)

title: low-carb peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a rapid boil for 1 minute and take off heat. Add the last 3 ingredients. Spoon onto wax paper and leave until set.

title: maureen's weight watcher chili
directions: In a saucepan, cook turkey and onion until brown.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer approximately 35 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Press 2 to 3 candies into top of cookie.
Bake at 325° for 13 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Can be refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: polenta
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Spread mixture in a square baking pan.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares when cool. Dip in beaten egg and milk.
Coat with fine bread crumbs.
Fry in vegetable oil until light brown.
Can also be used warm and served with spaghetti sauce.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put 1/4 of the water chestnuts in the middle when you are balling them up.
Brown meat balls in a skillet.
Take out and drain.
Put in a crock-pot and add barbecue sauce.
Cook on low, about 3 to 5 hours.

title: red flannel pickles
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boiling point.
Add pickles and pimentos and bring back to a boil.
Store in the refrigerator in a covered glass jar.
They will last 4 to 6 weeks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and make into ball. Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: velveeta cheese candy
directions: Melt cheese, margarine and vanilla in bowl.
Mix sugar and cocoa.
Pour cheese mixture over sugar.
Add nuts.
Pour in pan and press.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: mississippi mud pie(original recipe of mississippi river boat company)
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Mix flour and sugar. Add nuts (if desired), eggs and vanilla.
Pour in greased small glass pie pan and bake about 25 minutes at 350° or microwave on High for 3 minutes and 50 seconds.

title: squash pie
directions: Cut squash in pieces and boil until tender, then put in blender and then measure.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Pour in 2 (9-inch) deep crusts.

title: yummy easy custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (eggs, sugar, salt, milk and vanilla) in blender.
Mix on low speed.
Pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place on "pie saver" in oven.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In large stockpot (12-quart capacity) combine water, chicken broth, soup, chicken, onions, carrots, vermouth, garlic, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil; add tortellini.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broccoli; simmer an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender. Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 30 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: banana pudding(only 1 mg cholesterol per serving)
directions: Combine brown sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir one-fourth of hot milk into egg.
Add to remaining hot mixture.
Cook until thick.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cool.
Put layer of vanilla wafers, then layer of bananas and pour custard over.
Repeat layer.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pimiento cheese sandwich
directions: Cream grated cheese and pimiento.
Add enough mayonnaise to make mixture spread easily.
Season with salt, red pepper or chili powder, or Worcestershire sauce may be added for a more zippy spread.
Spread evenly on slices of bread.

title: muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and shortening and add to flour mixture, stirring only until mixed. Use tablespoon to dip batter into muffin tins.
Fill only 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: tostado dip
directions: Combine beans and sour cream; spread bean mixture in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients in order.
May be made ahead.
Serves best at room temperature.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add cream cheese, chili powder and salt. Simmer 5 minutes over medium heat.
Toss shells with butter.
Fill with beef mixture.
Arrange in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour taco salsa over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover; top with cheeses and chips.
Bake 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Add sour cream.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine rice, sauerkraut, corned beef and 1/2 cup of cheese in mixing bowl.
Mix mayo, pickle relish, mustard and salt and pepper.
Stir into rice mixture.
Turn into shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: low carb chicken filling
directions: Cook chicken strips in skillet thoroughly. Pour off drippings, leaving approximately 1/4 cup in pan. Add onion and green chiles; cook over medium heat for 3 minutes longer. Add cream cheese and seasonings; mix well and continue to simmer 5 to 7 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pare
and
slice
carrots.
Cook carrots and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain
and cool.	In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Add carrots.	Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pineapple, carrots and almonds. Blend mayonnaise with sour cream and seasonings; pour over chicken and toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly; arrange on salad greens and garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: salad(with main meal)
directions: Mix ingredients and place in casserole dish.

title: milky way salad
directions: Combine bananas, Cool Whip, candy bars and apples in a bowl. Sprinkle crushed cookies on top.
Chill as long as you like.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Cool and glaze.

title: banana-zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and oil.
Add bananas and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini and pecans just until combined.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle apples with nutmeg and cinnamon and 1/2 cup of sugar; add water.
Place in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Cream margarine and remaining sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Pat this mixture over apples and bake 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.
This is delicious served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Dip potatoes in Butter Buds.
Arrange on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: papa hobby's "kush"(icebox cookies)
directions: Put can of milk in refrigerator long enough to have crystallized, but not frozen.
Put bowl and beaters in refrigerator and get cold.
Crush wafers and spread in ice tray. Beat cold milk like whipped cream.
Add sugar until stiff.
Put in tray on top of crumbs, then top with crumbs.
Freeze.
Cut into servings.

title: basic sangria
directions: In a large pitcher, combine wine, brandy, Triple Sec, sugar and fruit.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Serve over ice.
If desired, add seltzer water to mixture in pitcher for a lighter quaff. Makes 6 drinks more if you add seltzer.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour pizza sauce over the hamburger meat, then put the Mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over the cheese. Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix lightly but well.
Sift flour and spices.
Add to moist mixture.
Add nuts and stir.
Bake in two well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Remove from oven and let cool on rack.

title: cottage cheese enchiladas with green sauce
directions: Blend green chilies, water, bouillon cube and romaine until pureed.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Simmer chili mixture until slightly thickened, about 3 minutes.
Stir often. Mix cottage cheese with 1 cup Jack cheese, cilantro and spices. Fry tortillas in lightly oiled skillet until softened.
Fill each with cheese mixture and roll.
Pour 2/3 of green sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish and place enchiladas in sauce.
Top with remaining sauce and 1 cup grated Jack cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cauliflower with roquefort
directions: Wash cauliflower.
Remove all outer green leaves and any dark or damaged parts on the head (try to select a head without these things in the first place).
Place in water with bouillon cubes and vinegar. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Shut off heat and allow to cool and marinate another 10 minutes. Remove the head whole from the liquor.
Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups of the liquor. Add about 1/8 teaspoon pepper or to taste.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 3 teaspoons per 6-ounce cup of hot water.
Attach recipe or instructions to jars.

title: no bake butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix canned milk, butter and sugar.
Cook over medium heat and stir until mixture bubbles well, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butterscotch chips (I used 2 packages). Stir until smooth.
Mix in corn flakes, crushed a little, nuts and coconut.
Drop quickly on wax paper and let set until firm.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Add lemon juice, milk, lemon rind, sugar replacement, salt and flour; beat until thoroughly blended.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour combined mixture into well-greased 1-quart baking dish.
Set dish in pan.
Add 1/2 inch water to pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes, until lightly browned and puffy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lower school lemonade
directions: If using lemons, squeeze the juice to get 1 cup lemon juice. Mix sugar, lemon juice and water in large pitcher.
Add cherry juice to make pink lemonade.
Pour lemonade over ice cubes in tall glasses.

title: hearty ham, cabbage chowder
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, saute celery, onion and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: mary louise jones casserole
directions: In the bottom of a 9 X 13 inch casserole dish, place six of the tortillas.
Spoon mixture over the top and sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Continue to layer in dish until gone.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 15-20 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
May add a layer of refried beans if desired.
Serves about 8.

title: sausage balls
