directions: Note:
Sausage needs to be at room temperature.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix remaining ingredients in 9 x 12 glass baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake 30 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix the
soup,	carrot,
onion and sour cream together. Melt margarine
and
mix
with bread mix.
Put layers of bread mix
in casserole,	beginning with and ending with bread mix. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: spooky hand treat
directions: Place one candy corn in each finger of the plastic glove (they will be the fingernails).
Fill the glove with popcorn and a few M&M's.
Tie the bag with black yarn.
Place the spider ring on a finger.
Now it is a spooky hand treat to eat.

title: hawk cove crab soup
directions: Combine milk, spices and lemon peel in top of a large double boiler.
Cook mixture over simmering water for 10 minutes.
Stir crabmeat, half & half, butter and salt into hot mixture.
Cook over boiling water for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in wine and serve immediately.

title: joan's jam sandwich cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, egg, almond flavoring.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and add to Crisco mixture.
Place half of the dough in an 8 inch square pan.
Cover with the strawberry jam.
Cut an 8 inch square of waxed paper and pat remaining dough onto it.
Flip this on top of the jam and peel off the waxed paper.
Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes.

title: angel food cake(this cake is heavenly.)
directions: In a bowl, add salt to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar, then fold in flour and flavoring.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon nut drop cookies
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add sugars.
Beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, peanut butter, syrup and vanilla; beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt; stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Pack dough into a 1/4-cup measure.
Drop dough 4 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Lightly press each cookie into a 3 1/2-inch circle with fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (centers of cookies will be slightly soft).
Cool slightly on cookie sheets. Remove to wire racks and cool completely.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: deluxe peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches and 1 cup sugar; stir well and set aside.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt; stir well.
Gradually add sugar mixture to eggs, beating until thick. Add milk; mix well.
Pour egg mixture in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Add peaches, stirring well.
Pour into chilled freezer can of 4 gallon freezer.
Freeze according to instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour together.
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over mixture and drizzle margarine over it.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato and onion bake
directions: Peel and thinly slice onion.
Place onion and butter in a microwave proof jug or bowl.
Cook on high for 2 minutes or until soft.
Wash and thinly slice the potatoes. Place half the potatoes, layered, on the bottom of a microwave proof dish. Top with onion, then arrange the remaining potatoes on top.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, cover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Spread with breadcrumbs and parmesan cheese.
Grill until golden.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well all except cream and let stand overnight.
Fold in cream when ready to use.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all softened cream cheese together.
Add other ingredients except 1 jar dried beef.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll balls in remaining jar of chopped dried beef.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: annette's coffee cake
directions: Add cake mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, sour cream, cooking oil and vanilla together in large mixing bowl.
Mix well with mixer for about 3 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix granulated sugar, pecans, cocoa and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured tube cake pan.
Add 1/2 sugar mixture and swirl with a knife (like a marble cake).
Add remaining 1/2 of batter and last half of sugar mixture.
Swirl again.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix Hellmann's mayonnaise and sour cream and pour over salad.

title: capintona eggplant appetizer
directions: Cube whole eggplants with peelings and steam until tender. Saute onions, bell peppers, celery and garlic in olive oil until wilted.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, wine vinegar and sugar. Blend and let cook for 10 minutes.
Add spice and seasonings to your taste.
Combine this mixture to eggplant and add salad olives. Bring to a good boil and remove from heat.
Place in jars immediately and seal.

title: hot crabmeat quiche
directions: Combine crabmeat, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Spread into shallow dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with saltines.

title: tutti fruity fruit cocktail
directions: Tutti Fruity Fruit Cocktail is great anytime you want it.
It is simple to make and nutritious, too.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Line with wax paper, then grease again.

title: barley meat
directions: Boil meat with a little salt and onion, using plenty of water. When done, remove meat from liquid.
To the liquid add barley. Cook until liquid is used and barley is soft.
While barley is cooking, grind the meats.
Combine meat and barley, adding more salt if desired.
(If fat is left in, it will slice better later.) Pack into ungreased loaf pans.
May be wrapped and frozen, or used at once.
To serve, slice into 1 inch slices.
Sprinkle with flour and pan fry, turning once.
This is a very old recipe but still a favorite.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian spareribs
directions: Mix flour, salt and soy sauce into paste.
Brush on ribs and set aside 10 minutes.
In large skillet brown all sides of ribs in oil.
Transfer ribs to roasting pan.
Drain fat from skillet and add sugar, vinegar, water, pineapple juice, garlic and ginger; heat thoroughly.
Pour over ribs and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Turn occasionally and place pineapple rings on top last 10 minutes.

title: killer pizza
directions: Prepare hot roll mix as directed on box.
Spread on pizza pan. Pour tomato sauce on dough and spread evenly, then sprinkle with garlic salt and Italian seasoning mix.
Add onion, bell pepper and mushrooms, then top with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes (or until cheese is melted and crust is brown).

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water and let cool.
Add sour cream and pineapple, stirring together.
Let cool and serve.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Cook sugar with milk and margarine in double boiler to soft ball.
Stir often.
Add to chips, Fluff, vanilla and nuts.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Spread beef in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with hash browns.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with onion rings; bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: mae oma jones' lasagne
directions: In hot Wesson oil in heavy pan, cook garlic and onion until soft.
Add beef and seasonings and cook until crumbly.
Mix in tomato paste and hot water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put a thin layer of sauce, half the noodles, all the cottage cheese and one half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with one half of remaining sauce, remaining noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Complete with the rest of the sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all together and put in pan. Top with additional chopped almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Heat ingredients, except pretzels; pour over pretzels.
Bake at 200° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chill shrimp and if large, cut in halves or quarters.
Toss together shrimp which has been combined with lemon juice, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Serve on lettuce and salad greens. Garnish top with shrimp and eggs.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, sugar, oleo and walnuts.
Blend into ball of dough; spread on pan.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: aunt marguerite's chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Criso.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Form into balls and roll heavy in confectioners sugar.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set pan aside.

title: dolly beck's green chili chicken enchilada casserole
directions: *Note:
You can tear 3 or 4 corn tortillas at a time into strips, then into pieces.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add salt, milk and finely grated onion.
Over medium to low heat, stir often.
Dice cheese and add to milk.
Dice potatoes in covered baking dish, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour melted cheese over potatoes to cover them.
If thick, add a little milk. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, last 15 minutes, uncover or until top starts to brown.

title: ranch casserole
directions: Mash tamales in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix hominy, beans and chili and pour over tamales.
Cover with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven until hot all the way through and cheese is well melted.

title: lo-cal cole slaw
directions: Toss lightly and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and cook noodles according to package instructions.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, layer 1/2 noodles, hamburger, celery and onion; repeat.
Combine all soups and heat. Pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put cashews on top for the final 15 minutes of baking.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add green onion dip and the next 4 ingredients, beating at medium speed until smooth.
Spoon potato mixture into a lightly greased 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and dip balls using a toothpick.
Place in fridge until chocolate hardens.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and brown hamburger.
Add salt, pepper and onion powder.
Mix macaroni with all sauces, sugar and oregano.
Put 1/2 in baking dish, then add layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining macaroni and another layer of Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pepperoni.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
(Can cook in microwave on High power 6 minutes per pound.)
Place half and half and water in the top of double boiler.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until all the cheese is melted.
Add broccoli.

title: cabbage pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make ahead so marshmallows turn soft.

title: raspberry jello delight
directions: Bring juice mixture to a boil and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls to the hot gelatin.
Stir until melted.
Chill until almost thickened.
Fold in drained berries.
Chill until firm.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl, stir together with fork flour, sugar and salt. Cut in shortening
with
fork
until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together water,
vinegar
and
egg.
Add
to
flour mixture and stir until
all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough in 5 portions and
with
hands
shape each in flat round patty ready for rolling.
Wrap
each
piece
in
wax paper and chill 1/2 hour. When you are ready to use, lightly flour both sides of patty roll on
pastry
sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 to
15 minutes.
(You can prevent soggy bottom crust
by baking pie on lowest
rack
in
oven
at
specified temperature in preheated oven.)

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel, slice and set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook onion and pepper in bacon drippings.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed and stir in. Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and water; boil 1 minute.
Add bacon.
Add hot mixture to potatoes and mix well.
Add pickle vinegar, salt or sugar to suit your taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a loaf pan, either 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch, with shortening, using a pastry brush. Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes, then loosen sides of pan and remove.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: out-of-this-world pie
directions: In pan, combine pie filling, sugar, pineapple with juice and cornstarch. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add gelatin. Stir well. When thoroughly cooled, add bananas and nuts. Pour into 2 pie shells. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt, then add hot raisin juice.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Roll into a ball in sugar and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef and rice
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in glass baking dish.
Mix remaining four ingredients with butter, then bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together; slice bananas on top.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Drain
pineapple, using juice for liquid with cake mix. Let cool.
Beat
cream	cheese	and
pudding
mix until thick. Spoon on	cake.
Then
spread
pineapple on.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.	Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.
Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: l b j ranch deer meat sausage
directions: Grind deer and hog meat and mix with remaining ingredients. Cook with scrambled eggs or form patties and pan-fry.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Melt margarine on low heat.
Add the chocolate chips and melt.
Add the egg mixture. Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Using rubber gloves, cut tops off peppers. Core center and rinse. Stuff each pepper with cheese. Mix egg, sausage and enough Bisquick to make a dough. Wrap sausage mixture around peppers. Roll in Shake 'n Bake and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta caponata
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add eggplant and garlic; saute until eggplant is well-browned, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to skillet along with onion and peppers.
Saute about 5 minutes, until the peppers and onion are softened and lightly browned.
Stir in drained tomatoes, broth, vinegar and capers.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepot of boiling, salted water, cook pasta as the package directs; drain.
Place in a large serving bowl and toss with the eggplant mixture.

title: frosted spice cake
directions: Beat egg whites and add 1 cup brown sugar.
Combine all other ingredients until well mixed and spread in a baking pan.
Spread the brown sugar-egg white mixture on cake mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: yum yum ball
directions: Melt margarine, then add peanut butter, graham crackers, sugar and vanilla.
Make into small balls and put on wax paper.
Put chocolate and wax in double boiler and let melt.
Then dip the balls in the chocolate and wax.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: tossed salad with vinaigrette dressing(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a large bowl toss all ingredients, except sesame seed. Pour vinaigrette over.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: crispy pecan-coconut clusters
directions: Spread pecans in a pie plate.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 4 to 5 minutes or until toasted, stirring after every minute. Set aside.

title: squash souffle
directions: Steam squash and onion.
Add milk, egg and seasonings.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee ice cream pie
directions: Crumble cookies.
Add instant coffee and melted butter.
Mix and press into a 9 inch pie pan.
Chill.
Crumble candy bars and mix with softened ice cream.
Press ice cream mixture into pie pan.
Add a layer of chocolate sauce.
Top with whipped topping.

title: nut sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar together. Add flour alternating with water and baking powder.

title: mable's pepper relish
directions: Heat vinegar, water and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Fill pint jars and seal tightly.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: This works really well in a crock-pot.

title: scottish marmalade cake
directions: Cream margarine until soft and add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix in marmalade, raisins and flour.
Pour into greased and bottom-lined deep 7-inch cake pan.
Level the surface.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 to 1-1/2 hours or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 15 minutes and turn out onto rack to cool completely.

title: meat and 'tater pie
directions: Prepare pie crust and line pie pan.
Combine meat, milk, dry soup mix, pepper and allspice.
Mix well.
Lightly pat into pastry-lined pie pan.
Top with potatoes.
Put on top crust and seal edges.
Cut slits into top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with warm catsup.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper in a saucepan with 2 cups of water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are just tender. Do not drain.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine apples, orange and pear.
Add raisins and pecans. Mix.
Add mayonnaise and mix thoroughly until all ingredients are evenly covered.
Chill and serve.

title: rhubarb refrigerator jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add Jell-O and pineapple and put in sterilized jars.
Refrigerate or can be frozen.
Use plastic containers for freezing.

title: treasure hunt mix
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in seasonings.
Put cereal and pretzels in a large flat pan.
Pour butter sauce over the cereal mixture, tossing to blend.
Bake uncovered in 250° (low) oven for 1 hour, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Add nuts the last 15 minutes.

title: lachen kugle
directions: Mix everything (in large bowl) with mixer except apples, raisins and noodles.
To first mixture, add remaining ingredients. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Served as a side dish with a main course.

title: cavatene
directions: Cook ground beef with the onion and mango.
Drain.
Add garlic powder, Italian seasoning and spaghetti sauce.

title: dorito crunch
directions: Cook meat and onions until done; drain and set aside.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325°.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Cream melted butter with sugar mixed with flour.
Grate rind of lemon and add to butter and sugar.
Squeeze and add juice.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add milk.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press out crescent rolls in a large pizza pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing; pour over cooled rolls.
Spread on mixed veggies over dressing; top with shredded cheese.

title: carrot balls
directions: Combine carrots, bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Toss lightly.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Fold into carrot mixture (mixture may be chilled at this time).
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and roll in cornflakes.
Place balls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in graham cracker crusts.
Chill before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add all other ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour into two pie crusts.
Place foil strips around crust edges.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until knife tip placed in center comes out clean.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and nuts mixed in.
Swirl over pie slices.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: new england apple cake
directions: In a large bowl beat together the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Blend together flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, blending well.
Dissolve baking soda in water.
Add to batter, combine well.
Add nuts and apples.
Combine well.
Batter will be very thick.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Dust with powdered sugar when completely cool.
Garnish with apple wedges.

title: pineapple-cherry cake
directions: Pour undrained pineapple into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple and sprinkle cake mix over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour melted margarine over cake top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix and bake orange cake as directed on box.
Bake in round cake pans.	Let cool.
Slice cake and make four layers.

title: cherry upside-down cake(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan well. Drain juice from black cherries and reserve it.
Place drained cherries and pecans in the pan.
In a medium sized mixing bowl, cream together the applesauce and honey.
Add eggs and milk and beat again.

title: no-time chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over moderate heat for 1 minute. Add onion and green pepper; saute, stirring often for 2 minutes or until slightly softened.
Add beef; stir and cook for 2 minutes or until no longer pink.
Pour off the fat.
Add seasoning mix and black pepper to saucepan.
Stir.
Cook over moderate heat for 1 minute.
Mix in tomatoes and kidney beans.
Bring to a simmer, stirring often.
Add green beans and red pepper flakes.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Cook rice according to package directions. Serve chili over rice and enjoy!

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together. Add the pecans, apples, coconut, raisins and pineapple. Pour into a large sheet pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1). Bake 1 hour at 325°. While the cake is still hot, pour the glaze over it.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: Saute onion, pepper and thyme in bacon grease until vegetables are tender. Stir in soup and water.
Add chicken and thyme to taste. Serve over rice.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef, add onions, peppers and cheese. Sift meal, salt and soda.
Combine sifted mixture with beaten eggs, milk, oil and corn.
Pour 1/2 bread mixture in a deep greased skillet or Corning Ware dish.
Add meat mixture, top with other 1/2 of bread mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fred's favorite zucchini
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add zucchini, onion, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook, covered, 12 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Combine with prepared chicken, cooked rice and broccoli.
Add mushroom soup, cheese soup, chicken broth and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: reindeer mix - snacks
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Melt chips and oil in microwave 2 minutes, stirring once.
Heat 10 seconds more until smooth. Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir until well coated.
Spread on wax paper covered cookie sheets to cool.

title: beer nuts
directions: Combine ingredients and boil until peanuts are coated and liquid is used up, stirring frequently.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with salt.	Bake 30 minutes at 350°; stir. Sprinkle with salt a few times while baking.
As they cool, stir again to avoid sticking.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Place over direct heat. Stir until dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla. Put in covered container; will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together all the ingredients with mixer.
Best when made night before serving.

title: wine-baked fillets
directions: *Fish Fillet Suggestions:
Cod, flounder, orange roughy, pike, sea bass, sole or whitefish.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings until golden; drain off excess fat and discard.
Add tomato paste, water, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and garlic salt.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine pork and beans, kidney beans and limas.
Add crumbled bacon, onion and celery sauce.
Stir to mix.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with bacon, onion and cheese. Cover with eggs and milk mixture.
Bake in middle of oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender.
Remove skin and bones, break into pieces.
Mix together the soup, cottage cheese, chiles, onion, tomatoes and chicken pieces.
In a 3-quart buttered casserole dish, place a layer of tortilla pieces.
Cover with a layer of soup and chicken mixture and a layer of grated cheese, repeat, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: taffy apple dessert
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Make sauce with pineapple juice, white vinegar, sugar, flour and egg.
Refrigerate overnight also.
The next day, combine sauce and pineapple mixture with the Cool Whip, diced apples and peanuts.
Mix together and refrigerate before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add all rest of the ingredients, pumpkin last.
Bake in Bundt cake pan for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard
directions: Pour hot milk over margarine; add sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and coloring. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Pour into deep pie crust, then sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 375°. Do not open oven door for 17 minutes. Pie is cooked when tip of paring knife comes out clean after inserting halfway between center and edge of pie.

title: chuck-wagon cabbage and apples
directions: Heat the bacon drippings in a 12-inch cast-iron Dutch oven over medium heat on the stove top (or a fire or hot coals).
Add the onion and cabbage.
Cook, covered, over just enough heat to steam the cabbage for 25 to 30 minutes, or until tender.
Stir occasionally to keep the onion from browning too much.
Stir in the apples, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Cover and continue to cook over low heat for another 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the apples are soft and cooked down.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: garlic salad dressing
directions: Mix salad dressing and sour cream with lemon and garlic.
Let stand one day.

title: low-fat apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs; add vanilla, applesauce, apple juice and apples.
Blend in dry ingredients. Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Brown beef and pour off excess fat.
Place a layer of beef, then a layer of potatoes, then a layer of onion, then a layer of peas in a square casserole dish.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven, covered, for 30 minutes, then bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald half the milk and add 1/2 cup of the sugar and the salt. Bring to a boil.
Mix flour, cornstarch and beaten egg and yolks with remaining milk. Beat until smooth. Add a little of the hot milk until blended.
Combine both mixtures together and cook over hot water until thick, stirring frequently.
Remove and add the butter and flavorings.
Beat until smooth.

title: easy blueberry dump cake
directions: Put berries in oblong type, greased pan.
Cover with pineapple.
Pour dry cake mix over this and top with broken nuts. Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: salad vinaigrette(dressing)
directions: Whisk mustard and vinegar in bowl.
Add oil and continue to blend.
Stir in garlic and whisk until creamy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Can be made ahead.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all vegetables together in a large bowl.
Pour Italian dressing over the vegetables and toss lightly.
Store, covered, in refrigerator for 2 days.
Drain before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apple cake in a jar
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order given. Sterilize 7 to 9 wide-mouth pint jars and lids. Grease jars with shortening. Fill jars half full. Bake on middle rack in oven for 45 minutes at 325°. As soon as the cakes are done, remove jars one at a time from oven. Wipe rim of jars clean with a damp cloth and put on the hot sterile lid. Screw down the bands and let cool. DO NOT USE SMALL-MOUTH JARS. DO NOT ADD ANY OTHER INGREDIENTS. As cake cools, it will pull away from the sides of the jars. SHELF LIFE IS ONE YEAR.

title: stuffed camel
directions: Stuff eggs into tomatoes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour half and half into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours until set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and chocolate shavings.
Makes 8 servings.

title: multi-grain bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: Heat water, yogurt and vegetable oil to boiling.
Stir in oats, wheat germ and bran.
Set aside until cooled to very warm (125° to 130°), about 30 minutes.

title: judy's pineapple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla, pineapple and juice. Add nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned corn meal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Sift together corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine egg, buttermilk and vegetable oil. Add to corn meal mixture, stirring to dry ingredients.
Fill greased medium muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in 420° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vietnamese grilled hens
directions: Cut the hens into halves.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and rub all over the hen halves.
Let these marinate for a few hours, turning them regularly.
Grill over charcoal or oak.
Serve with a dry Gewurztraminer or dry Riesling.
Serves 2.

title: spinach balls(a real crowd pleasing appetizer)
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Make into balls (walnut size). Freeze on cookie sheet.
After they are frozen, they will hold shape while you cook them.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Slice up apples in large bowl; add sugar substitute, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and butter.
Mix together.
Place crust in pie plate.
Line bottom of plate with a little flour.
Pour ingredients into crust.
Bake for 50 minutes at 425°.

title: vegetable chili con carne
directions: In large heavy skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until vegetables are soft.
Brown meat and add.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes and puree and all seasonings.
Heat mixture until bubbly. Reduce heat; cover the pan and simmer the chili for about 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans, jalapeno peppers, green peppers, carrots and celery.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.
Add corn to pot after ten minutes.

title: spicy punch
directions: Combine apple juice, cranberry juice cocktail and the spices in saucepan and bring just to a boil.
Serve hot in punch cups or mugs.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Chop cranberries, pineapple with liquid and sugar together in blender.
Pour into Jell-O mixture.
Add apple and pecans.
Refrigerate until set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Combine with buttermilk and pudding mix. Mix gently with fruits and refrigerate.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Cook onions, peppers, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large baking pan, place chicken on bottom of pan.
Mix soups and evaporated milk, then pour over chicken.
Pour stuffing on chicken mix. Then mix butter and broth and pour over stuffing. (Mix in broth, salt, pepper, onion salt, garlic powder, then pour.)
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix flour, rolled oats, brown sugar and oleo with mixer until crumbly.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain and cut squash in 1/4-inch slices and cook 5 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer 1/2 meat, 1/2 squash and 1/2 cup cheese; combine soup and liquid. Layer meat, squash and soup and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: gourmandise cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
In small mixer bowl, beat softened Gourmandise, cream cheese and reserved pineapple juice until well blended.
Stir in pineapple; chill thoroughly.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers and fresh fruit slices.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/2 stick oleo, milk and vanilla.
Spoon into 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 cup oleo.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beer bread
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; add beer and mix well.
Batter will be thick and lumpy.
Pour in a greased 9 x 5 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Place butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add sour cream and sugar and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water 5 minutes; stir sour cream mixture.
Add beaten eggs. Combine flour and salt gradually.
Add yeast mixture; mix well. Cover dough and refrigerate overnight.
Punch dough down; divide dough into 2 parts, shaping into any desired shape rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 20.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Put all together.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with peas and add a white sauce.

title: judy's spice cake
directions: Mix with a spoon in a large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours. (Cake is done when nicely browned and has pulled away from sides of pan.)

title: broiled crab sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients except English muffins.
Mix well. Spread about 1/4 cup of crab mixture and top of each muffin half. Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat until cheese melts (about 2 to 3 minutes).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add remaining ingredients with mixer. Add shrimp by hand.

title: macaroni slaw
directions: Gently toss together all ingredients.
Cover; chill several hours.
Makes 7 cups.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Combine rice and water in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Salt and pepper chicken and arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Put vegetable shortening into bowl; add hot water.
Mix shortening	until
melted
and
add flour and salt.
Mix well. Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Pierce skin of squash about 4 times.
Cook whole squash 8 to 10 minutes until soft to touch.
Cut in half; remove seeds. Season or fill with desired filling.
Cook covered 5 to 6 more minutes.

title: stir-fried scallops and vegetables
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well. Set aside.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 6 tortilla shells.
Brown meat and onion.
Combine meat, onion, tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Spread over shells in pan.
Combine 1 cup Cheddar cheese and cottage cheese.
Spread over top of mixture in pan.
Lay 3 tortilla shells over top.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup Cheddar cheese over shells. Bake covered with foil at 375° for 20 minutes.
(Use glass baking dish.)

title: creole cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs in separate bowl.
In different bowl, mix flour, salt and cocoa.
Mix buttermilk and vanilla together. Combine all together, then add soda to boiling water and pour into other ingredients (grease pan).
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
(Use buttermilk icing.)

title: spiced tea(beverage)
directions: Boil, cover and steep.

title: cheesy chicken primavera
directions: In large skillet stir-fry broccoli and carrots in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add squash and asparagus; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add Velveeta cheese, half and half and oregano.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add cooked chicken cubes, pepperoni, macaroni and Parmesan.
Stir lightly and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Bring salad, oil, white vinegar, sugar, Italian seasonings, salt, pepper and dry onions to a boil.
Let cool.
Add carrots, artichokes and mushrooms.
Marinate 24 hours.
Take this to a party, there won't be a drop left.

title: cowboy quiche
directions: Lightly grease the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients in following order in bottom of pan:
1/2 of the chilies, 1/2 of the grated cheese, remaining chilies, remaining cheese. Beat eggs, flour and milk together.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and chilies. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Allow quiche to set for 20 minutes before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Drain and add soup, mushroom slices, sour cream and cheese.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and add to mixture.

title: ham 'n cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until blended. Spread 1/4 of mixture on 1 ham slice; repeat with remaining cheese mixture and ham slices. Roll up from short side; chill for several hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Wet hands to mix ingredients.
Form into ball.
Place in fridge overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: pizza crust(makes two 12-inch crusts)
directions: Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and 1 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; let rise until double in size.
Punch down; divide in half. Flatten each half in pizza pan (greased).
Cover with pizza sauce. Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: In saucepan, bring to slow boil; set aside to cool. Separately beat 4 egg whites; add cooled mixture to egg whites. Top your pudding pie and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: baked sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake in oven of 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: new fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 12 minutes.

title: pretzel surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first three ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch glass container.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: flip
directions: Crush graham crackers and add melted butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Boil raspberries, 1/4 cup margarine, white sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Cool; add vanilla.
Mix together all the rest of the ingredients.
Mix until crumbly.
Pack 3/4 mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour filling on top and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone it and put in diced potatoes and corn.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Put in 2 tablespoons crushed rosemary, salt and pepper.
Put in bow tie noodles and cook until tender.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Fill crock-pot with apples and cook overnight on slow.
Add sugar and spices. Cook on slow for 8 hours.
Pour in jars.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix beaten eggs, oil and sugar together.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add apples, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Blend well by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and pour over macaroni:

title: baked beans
directions: Fry the bacon.
Crumble into beans.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add to bean mixture.
Add remaining ingredients to beans. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Then bake at 250° for another hour.

title: gelatin party dessert
directions: Dissolve 1 package each of lime, lemon and strawberry jello in 1 1/2 cups of hot water in 3 separate shallow pans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut brownie
directions: Melt butter and white chocolate in small saucepan. In a separate bowl, beat eggs and salt until foamy. Add sugar and mix until thick (90 seconds). Add chocolate mixture and beat 5 minutes. Add flour and mix just until moist. Fold in nuts. Pour into 8 X 8 greased pan and bake 40 minutes at 325 degrees. Drizzle sauce over top.

title: chili pie casserole
directions: Pour chili and tomato soup into 1 qt. boiler. Stir in green pepper. Cover and heat for 3 minutes. While chili is heating place half of chips in a 1 1/2 qt. glass casserole dish. Arrange onion and half of cheese over chips. Pour heated chili mixture over onion and cheese. Top with remaining chips and cheese. Cover and heat for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: steak in mushroom soup
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt, garlic and tenderizer.
Place uncut aluminum foil in baking dish.
Put mushroom soup over, spreading out as much as possible. Fold foil over and seal.
Cook in oven at about 300° to 350°, depending on cooking time.
If you have the time, let it cook slowly for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Place in large saucepan and cook on top of stove, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and is very thick.
Pour into glass baking dish and brown in oven at 450° until knife comes out clean.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Stir in the next 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken and spoon sauce over pieces.
Cover skillet and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Turn chicken and cook for 15 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Add spices to meat while browning.
Put 1 can golden mushroom soup into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add beef.
Layer vegetables over beef.
Sprinkle mushrooms over top of vegetables. Add last can of mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Cover with foil and cook for 3 or 4 hours on 250°.
(Can add layer of diced celery to vegetables, if desired.)

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes and cornflakes. Mix potatoes throughout the combined ingredients. Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and sprinkle corn flakes over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10. This is great when made ahead of time and baked at last minute. May be reheated and tastes even better the next day.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars together.
Add egg and peanut butter; then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each with a fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: macaroon cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl combine first three ingredients.
Mix at low speed until well combined, mixture will be crumbly.
Press evenly into bottom of greased pan.
In small bowl, combine condensed milk, vanilla and egg; beat until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup coconut and nuts; pour mixture over crust.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup coconut over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 36 bars.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix shortening and egg.
Add milk.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Place in greased or Pam sprayed pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add diced potato and eggs; scramble all together.
Place generous amount of cooked mixture in steamed tortilla.

title: freezer cabbage slaw
directions: Mix cabbage,
carrot,
pepper
and
salt and let stand. Boil sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed for 1 minute.
Cool and mix into slaw.	Freeze.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: feta cheese sticks(from:  janie anagnostis)
directions: Knead cheese, flour, butter and pepper by hand about 15 minutes, until dough is soft, but not sticky.
Roll by hand into rectangular shapes.
Cut into 6-inch strips.
Twist each and place on cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sesame seed or paprika.
Bake in 400° preheated oven approximately 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as usual and let partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together well and place in mold.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: *cheesecake cookies
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour and walnuts.
Mix in melted butter.
Save out about 1/3 cup of the crumbs.
Pat mixture into bottom of pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mormon muffins
directions: In a bowl, stir baking soda in water until dissolved. Cool. In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after

each addition. Combine flour and salt. Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk. Mix well. Beat in baking soda mixture. Fold in cereals and nuts. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Yields 5 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasoning mix.
Cool and drain.
Combine lettuce, meat, cheese and olives.
Add dressing and chips when ready to serve.

title: cream filled chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour into paper-lined muffin tins, about 2/3 full.
Cream the sugar and cream cheese until smooth, then add the egg and mix well.
Add the chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture onto each cupcake. Bake cupcakes according to package directions.
When finished baking, the filling will be in the middle of each cupcake.
Frost with your favorite frosting.
These make great birthday treats for your kids to take to school.
Makes about 24-30 cupcakes.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter or oleo. Cover a thin layer of crumbs with oysters. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add some of liquid and cream. Repeat layers and top with crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 450°. May double or triple this recipe to make a nice size casserole. This recipe will only serve about 4 people.

title: squash muffins
directions: Drain cooked, mashed squash to consistency of mashed potatoes. Cream the sugar, syrup and butter.
Add egg and squash; blend. Mix or sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Beat with squash batter and fold in pecans if used.
Fill muffin pans that have been greased or sprayed with cooking spray about half full; bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 15.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot, stirring together after cheese had been melted.
Serve with chips or crackers or your choice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, fruit cocktail, sugar and then dry parts. Pour into 9-inch cake pans, then top with last three ingredients onto the cake mixture.
Bake at 275° for 75 minutes.

title: delicious chicken breast
directions: Choose as many chicken breasts as you want.
Put 1 slice of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Pour cream of chicken soup over cheese.
Sprinkle heavily with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: gracie's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except tomato sauce.
Shape into 1 or 2 loaves.
Place into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour tomato sauce onto loaf.
Bake for another 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and salt in pan. Mix egg yolks and milk then add to dry ingredients. Cook over medium heat until thickened stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla and oleo. Pour into baked crust. Top with egg white meringue and brown.

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in oleo, coat with bread crumbs and seasonings.
Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: chili sauce
directions: In a large pot, put tomatoes, vinegar and sugar; let heat. Add onions, salt, mustard, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, paprika and red pepper; mix thoroughly. Let cook down low to desired thickness, being careful not to let it stick. Put into hot clean pint jars and seal. This will make about 8 pints.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine flour, yeast and caraway seed.
Stir together water, brown sugar, cooking oil and salt in separate bowl.
Add flour mixture.
Beat at low speed.
Then beat 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in rye flour and as much all-purpose flour as you can mix in with a spoon.
Flour surface and knead dough, adding flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
Punch down and divide in half.
Cover; let rise 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breast until done then debone. Add all the other ingredients and mix well. Add mayonnaise and relish as needed to get it to the desired consistency. Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: best vanilla ice cream
directions: Heat milk in a 3-qt. saucepan over low heat until hot. Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually add sugar mixture to milk, stirring until well blended. Cook over medium heat 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: potato and carrot medley
directions: In heavy 3-quart pan, melt butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to combine.
Cook, covered, over medium-low heat for 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields four 1-cup servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crumbs and 1 stick of butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining butter, powdered sugar and eggs in small bowl.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Spread pineapple over filling.
Spread bananas over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas and top with cherries and walnuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add syrup to eggs; stir in sugar, salt and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels with water and margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently until sauce is smooth.
Combine sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Gradually add caramel sauce; mix well. Stir in nuts; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Pie filling will appear to be very soft, but becomes firm as it cools.

title: chocolate fudge layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan over low heat. Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add chocolate mixture, buttermilk and eggs.
Beat on low for 1 minute.
Beat on high until light and fluffy (2 minutes). Pour batter into pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 5 minutes.
Then put on wire rack.

title: icebox cake
directions: Melt crushed candy with coffee cream in a double boiler. While hot, add gelatin soaked in cold water.
Let cool and add the whipped cream.
Line a loaf pan with cookies.
Make alternate layers of cookies and filling.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken skin side up in a 12 x 7 x 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt. Blend wine into mushroom soup. Add mushrooms and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Remove chicken to platter. Sprinkle with paprika. Pour sauce from baking dish into saucepan. Blend in sour cream and heat gently until hot. Serve chicken with hot cooked rice and top with sauce.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and
flour
two 9-inch pie pans.
Beat eggs well and add
sugar,
flour,
milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Mix well. Stir in coconut.
Divide mixture in the two greased and floured pans.
Bake
at
for
25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ground beef and vegetable casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion.
Add pepper to taste. Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and water; simmer for 15 minutes. Pour into large casserole dish.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Stir in cooked vegetables (cook vegetables as directed on package). Separate biscuits into 20; overlap biscuits around the outside of dish.
Spread an additional 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese on the center.
Bake for 22 to 27 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Prepare stuffing.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons on each slice of turkey and roll up.
Place in dish seam side down.
Prepare soup and pour over rolls.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well.
Add chocolate.
Mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add chocolate mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat well after each addition.
Add water; mix well. Stir in vanilla.
Batter will be thin.

title: kopper karrots
directions: Bring pot of salted water to boil and add handful of dill stems.
Add new potatoes.
(Water should not entirely cover potatoes; it should cover only about 2/3 of each potato.) cover with lid and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are just barely tender.

title: crostata
directions: Make crust by combining flour, sugar, salt, butter, shortening, egg and lemon peel.
Roll out dough, keeping it at least 1/4 inch thick.
Line pie pan, having about 1-inch edge. Spread thin coat of preserves over unbaked crust.
Arrange apple slices in overlapping rings to cover the crust (one layer).
Drop several spoons of preserves over apples and spread carefully to keep apples in place.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven until crust is golden brown.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered milk.
Shape into small balls. Roll balls in coconut. Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: sweet potato salad(low-fat!)
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, cumin and salt in a medium size bowl. Add remaining ingredients except for the whole parsley.
Toss very carefully so that the sweet potatoes stay intact.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Garnish with parsley just before serving. Serves 4.
Tastes great and great for you, too!

title: mexican salsa
directions: Skin tomatoes, core and remove as many seeds as possible. Process in food processor until almost puree.
Pour into nonmetallic bowl; add vinegar, salt, pepper and cumin.
Chop onion, mince garlic and add to bowl.
Clean peppers, mince in processor.
Add to bowl.

title: toll house outrageous snack cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine butter, oats, flour, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in half of the chocolate chips.
Spread batter in ungreased 8-inch square microwave-safe dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 more minutes, until top of cake appears dry and bottom is even color.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over cake.
Cool directly on counter top.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with layer of Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Melt margarine and drizzle on top.
Bake at 325° for one hour, covered, then uncover and bake another 1/2 hour. Serves 4.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in 3 round cake pans. Put a layer of cake in punch bowl.
Add layer of each ingredient. Add another cake layer, etc.
Finish off top layer with Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Add one cherry to give look of a sundae.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: In large pot, cook first 4 ingredients; cool.
Into same pot, add flour and baking soda.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured) at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: brownie dump bars
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla; add remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top before baking.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Serve with cut vegetables and Hawaiian bread.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust and crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: garlic butter potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cube into pieces about 1 inch.
Do not peel. Put into a covered casserole dish.
Drop in 1 stick butter. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour in milk.
Cover. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Do not lift lid.
The steam helps cook.
Take out of oven and let sit for 30 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except beans and simmer 20 minutes. Combine with beans. Place in buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: "pecan pie"
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar together.
With a fork or wire whisk, add eggs and blend them in.
Add cornstarch, salt and vanilla.
Add corn syrup, followed by the pecans.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: skinny strawberry cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend yogurt and cottage cheese in blender.
Beat eggs, salt, vanilla, sugar and flour.
Stir in yogurt mixture.
Pour into pie crust and bake 50 minutes or until custard is set.
Cool, then refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. Garnish with strawberries or fruit glaze.
Yields 8 servings with 370 calories and 20 g fat per serving.

title: dena's curry fruit bake
directions: Cut and drain fruit except bananas for several hours or overnight.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and curry powder.
Peel and cut bananas into salad size pieces.
Mix with other fruit; add melted butter with fruit and sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Mix lightly.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with ham, baked chicken or any meat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamy vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions; drain and place in a large bowl. Stir in soup and cream cheese. Transfer to a greased 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with croutons. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese-olives
directions: Blend the cheese, butter and Worcestershire, then the flour and salt.
Now tidily wrap each olive in bits of the resultant paste.
Spread the little balls out in a pan to freeze until they're hard, about 1 hour.
Finally, bake them at 425° for 12 minutes and serve them hot.
Can freeze unbaked.

title: tomato-curry chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown in butter.
Transfer to 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add onion, pepper, garlic, curry and thyme.
Cook over medium heat for 9 minutes. Add tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook slowly together until tender, hamburger, onion, green pepper and celery.
When thoroughly done, add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and salt and pepper.
Cook mostaccioli according to box directions. Combine with meat mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. The next day add V-8 juice.
Mix. Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Lay all of cheese, sliced, on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is hot and bubbly and slightly brown, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced ham
directions: Wash gammon and soak in cold water for 1/2 hour.
Mix mustard, cinnamon and brown sugar and spread on gammon.
Put in casserole with enough orange juice to almost cover.
Cover dish and bake until gammon is tender.
Core apples but do not peel.
Cut in quarters and cook gently in remainder of juice.
Remove apples and arrange on top of gammon; keep hot.
Thicken juice with blended cornflour.
Serve with gammon.
Makes 2 servings.
Oven Temperature:
190° C. Position in Oven:
Middle shelf.

title: chicken or turkey dressing casserole
directions: Boil fryer
or
turkey and debone.
Reserve 2 quarts of broth. Mix
white
corn
meal
as
directed.
Add
onions and celery. Bake
this
as
directed
on corn bread mix.
Crumble cornbread and
combine
with
Pepperidge Farm crumbs, poultry seasoning, salt
and pepper.
Stir in chopped eggs.
Spoon 1/2 into 2-quart baking
dish.
Layer with chicken or turkey then the rest of the dressing mix.
Cover top with cream of chicken soup and add a little water.
Bake until bubbly at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Reserved broth may be used for homemade soup.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown hamburg with onion and minced garlic.
Add rest of ingredients and let simmer for an hour or more.

title: vinegar roll
directions: Mix flour
and	shortening.
Mix
milk, water, salt and soda. Add to flour to make dough.
Divide dough into 4 parts. Roll each piece
of
dough
as
for pie.
Sprinkle each pastry circle with 1/3
cup
sugar, 3 pats oleo and 3 teaspoons vinegar.
Roll
up. Pinch
ends together.
Place in buttered pan. Pour remaining sugar,
vinegar and oleo on top.
Pour two cups boiling water over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: blender custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender jar and blend well.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tangy wings
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add BBQ sauce, honey and soy sauce.
Pour over cooked wings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions, saving the juice.
Combine with juice and other ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes. Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt butter in roasting pan.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereals, nuts and pretzels, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels or a brown grocery bag to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: crinkle top molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients and beat until batter is well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: spaghetti squash primavera
directions: With fork, prick surface of spaghetti squash. Place in large kettle; cover with cold water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered 50 to 55 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: celery-chicken stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks and set the egg whites aside.
Mash the egg yolks with a fork.

title: low-fat vegetable soup
directions: Combine zucchini, carrots, mushrooms, onion and potato in heavy, large Dutch oven.
Add vegetable broth, crushed and stewed tomatoes, 3 tablespoons parsley, cilantro, garlic, basil and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes.
Strain cooking liquid into large saucepan; reserve vegetables.
Place 3 cups vegetables in blender. Add 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Pure until smooth.
Stir pure into remaining liquid in saucepan.
Return vegetables to liquid. Season with salt and pepper.
Bring soup to simmer and ladle into bowls. Sprinkle with additional parsley.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together (dry).
Beat egg yolks lightly and add sugar.
Combine with buttermilk and butter (melted).
Beat egg whites stiff and add to mixture last.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: schaum torte
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until glossy.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Fill with berries and top with whipped cream.

title: furniture polish
directions: Select him with care.
Do not spoil him by mismanagement in cooking.
Do not keep him constantly in hot water, or let him freeze by icy indifference.
To make him tender, see that his linen is nicely washed, starched, ironed and mended, all buttons and snaps sewn on and put in place.

title: interstate 20 crisp-baked chicken
directions: Combine wheat germ, cornflake crumbs, onion salt, dill weed and pepper on a sheet of waxed paper; mix well.
Turn buttermilk into a shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces first in buttermilk, then in crumb mixture, coating all sides.
Arrange in a flat baking pan in a single layer.
Drizzle melted butter over chicken pieces. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) about 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast rolls (sticky buns)
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Drop in rolls.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts with melted oleo.
Drizzle over rolls. Cover with towel, set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spring temptation pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add orange sherbet until melted. Chill until gelatin soft set. Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pineapple. Chill.

title: corn salad
directions: Chill corn.
Add other ingredients, as much as you desire.

title: farm house breakfast
directions: Cut links into fourths; spread on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan (glass).
Cover with scrambled eggs.
Cover with cottage cheese, then cover with Cheddar cheese soup.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot with toast, muffins or bread.
Simple and elegant.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine everything.
Start with 1 cup buttermilk, depending on how thick or thin you want your pancakes.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per package directions.
Rinse and drain; set aside.
Slice green and red pepper in strips.
Slice olives in rings.
Chop onions including green stems.
Cut artichokes and tomatoes in half.
Mix all vegetables and toss with pasta and Italian dressing.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Add raisins to cold water and boil until nearly all water is absorbed by raisins.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix well.
Pour into well greased bundt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Conventional Method:
Combine water and gelatin in a 1-quart saucepan. Heat until gelatin dissolves.
Stir lemon extract, lemon peel and Equal into gelatin mixture.
Set aside.

title: chocolate marshmallow dessert
directions: Mash graham crackers.
Sprinkle half in bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan or shallow dish.
Beat egg whites stiff; add marshmallow, cut fine and nuts.
Pour this mixture over crumbs.
Beat egg yolks; add sugar, butter and chocolate sauce.
Put this on top of egg white mixture; cover with remaining crumbs and let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Do not freeze.

title: mounds candy
directions: Stale angel food cake can be cut into 1/2-inch slices and shaped with cookie cutters to make delicious "cookies." Just toast in the oven for a few minutes.

title: chicken with raspberry sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/2 cup preserves, raspberry vinegar, pineapple juice, soy sauce, balsamic vinegar, garlic and seasonings; mix well. Remove 1 cup for sauce; cover and refrigerate.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Fry until golden brown in heavy skillet in shortening.
Fry slowly so as not to burn grease and turn only once.

title: chocolate chip zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs with sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients; stir in zucchini, raisins, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
I line a loaf pan with waxed paper.
Will make 2 loaves.
Freezes well.
Enjoy.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into small balls and flatten with a fork. (It helps if you cool the batter down a little in the fridge.) Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 325° for 10 minutes (maybe a little longer) or until golden brown. Yield: 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice and spread in greased 9 x 13 pan. Heat soups and milk and pour over rice. Layer chicken breast over soups. Sprinkle dry soup mix over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 350 degrees for 2
1/2 hours.

title: asparagus strata
directions: Using a doughnut cutter, cut 12 circles and holes from bread; set aside.
Tear remaining bread in pieces and place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer cheese, asparagus and ham over torn bread; arrange bread circles and holes in top.
Lightly beat eggs with milk.
Add onion, salt and mustard; mix well. Pour egg mixture over bread circles and holes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes or until top is light golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: steak san marco
directions: In large skillet, arrange meat; cover with Lipton onion soup mix and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder, pepper, oil and vinegar.
Simmer covered 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic chocolate cake
directions: Place bran, water, sugar substitute, egg, vegetable oil, vanilla, chocolate flavoring and lemon juice in a mixer bowl; mix lightly.
Let stand for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Timing is very important.)
Combine flour, soda, cocoa, sugar, dry milk, cinnamon and salt.
Stir to blend well.
Add flour mixture to bran mixture; mix at medium speed about 1/2 minute or until well blended.

Place in a well-greased 9-inch square cake pan; bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until the cake springs back when touched in the center and the sides of the cake pull away from the sides of the pan.
Cool to room temperature and cut 3 x 4-inch squares to yield 12 squares.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: In a a large mixing bowl combine four and sugar. Add potatoes, eggs, corn syrup, nutmeg, salt, margarine and
milk. Beat well. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes. Serves 8. Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: orange butter icing
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Spread on with spatula or pastry brush.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook, without stirring, for
5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda (will foam up) and vanilla. Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well. Turn onto two cookie sheets.
Bake in slow oven (200°), stirring every 15 minutes until done. Cool.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In skillet, melt butter and mix in onions, peppers, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Let simmer 5 minutes and add rest of ingredients and bring to boil, about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve plain or on rice.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar replacement.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg in sifter; add alternately with hot apple juice to creamed mixture. Fold in raisins and currants.
Allow to rest 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet, 2 to 3-inches (5 to 7 cm) apart.
Bake at 350°F (170°C) for 12 to 15 minutes. Yield: 60 cookies.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter and sugars together at medium speed.
Add egg and all other ingredients except nuts and white chocolate.
Mix until well blended, then add nuts and white chocolate.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets (may use vegetable spray).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack to finish cooling.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: pea salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix together 1 teaspoon each:
olive oil, sugar and vinegar.

title: dru's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Cream in egg. Add vanilla. Sift flour and soda gradually into creamy mixture. After well blended, pinch off thumb-sized pieces and roll into ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Makes about 40 cakes.

title: easy rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O and pudding in 3 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
Add cold, drained pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: grama cookies
directions: Soften butter or margarine.
Measure all ingredients except dates and nuts.
With mixer at low speed, beat until mixed. Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Preheat oven to 375°. Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Remove after 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot cheese steak
directions: Brown steak cubes, pepper and onion in a skillet.
Melt Velveeta and Ro-Tel tomatoes in a pan over medium heat.
(For a milder cheese sauce, use less Ro-Tel.)
When cheese is melted, add to steak in skillet, then pour in your uncooked Minute rice. Simmer over low heat until rice is cooked, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Place one wafer in cupcake paper.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Set in muffin pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: In large casserole, put cooked veggies and chicken.
Add 1/2 can onion rings.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over casserole.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Top with rest of can of onion rings.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
tags: cream of broccoli with cheese soup

title: "goodbye" turkey
directions: Sift flour, half of salt and onion salt into butter.
Stir in milk.
Cook over hot water, stirring occasionally until thickened. Pour Minute rice into 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine broth, remaining salt and pour over rice.
Sprinkle half of cheese over rice.
Top with asparagus or peas, then turkey.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Top with almonds.

title: black bean chili
directions: Brown meat, drain.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, carrots.
Add pepper, dried onion flakes, chili powder to taste. Simmer.
Serve with cooked rice if desired.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk and bring to full boil for 1 minute on medium heat.
Remove from heat.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream together milk, lemon juice, Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix pumpkin and eggs.
Add flour mixture and pumpkin mixture alternately to sugar and oil.

title: chicken-liver spread
directions: Put chicken livers in saucepan and cover with cold water.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, bring to boil and simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain and chop fine.
Simmer onion in the tomato juice for 15 minutes. Mix livers, onion and remaining ingredients and whirl in blender until smooth.
Pack in bowl and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups, 18 calories per tablespoon.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo and the confectioners sugar in mixer.
Drop one egg at a time into the mixer until all have been added.
Add flour, a cup at a time.
Beat well.
Add flavoring of choice. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes or until done.

title: festive fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan the sugar, evaporated milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over the top). Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a greased 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: In a skillet, melt butter and add chopped onions and celery. Cook slowly until slightly browned.
In baking dish, put in mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and rice.
Mix well.
Add onions and celery and slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut breasts in half. Place chicken between plastic wrap and pound to 1/4 inch thick. Place one slice of ham and one slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Roll up carefully and secure with wooden pick.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat the chicken rolls in flour mixture. Dip chicken roll in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs.

title: peppered steak
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika.
Brown in butter with garlic pieces; add broth and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in onion and green peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened and broth has a shiny look.
Add tomatoes and stir in gently just long enough to heat tomatoes through.
Serve over rice.
