title: beef and bagel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with torn up honey wheat bagels.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/4 cup sauce mixture into a greased 10-inch casserole dish.
Combine potatoes and remaining ingredients in big bowl.
Layer half the potato mixture over sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 8.

title: cocoa candy cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and mix together.
Spoon out on wax paper to cool.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil rice in rapidly boiling water to cover for 10 minutes, mix with chili con carne and salt.
Select medium size head cabbage with loose leaves, cut around heart; cook in boiling water until leaves wilt, about 6 minutes.
Cool.
Separate leaves.
Place 2 tablespoons of chili mixture on cabbage leaf, fold edges over; roll.
Place rolls in large buttered casserole; cover with remaining ingredients mixed.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until gravy is heavy.
Yields 12 or more servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice up potatoes and onion.
Put in kettle of water.
Cook until done.
Drain all but one inch of water from kettle.
Add milk (as much as there was water before draining).
Add corn, butter, salt and pepper.
Don't let milk boil.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook various shapes and sizes of your favorite pasta.
Drain and place in large bowl.
While pasta is hot, add your favorite frozen (yes frozen) mixed vegetables (veggies will cool the pasta as they thaw).
Add honey mustard vinaigrette dressing to taste. Add cheese.
Toss and enjoy.

title: macaroni, cheese and hamburger dish
directions: Fix macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
While this is cooking, fry hamburger.
Add cooked hamburger to macaroni and cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Serve while hot.

title: merry's cinqo de mayo tex-mex dip
directions: Mix 1/2 package of taco seasoning mix with "light" cream cheese; spread in bottom of microwavable pie plate.
Mix remaining 1/2 package of taco seasoning with small can of refried beans. Spread as next layer.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and 1 1/4 cups sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Cut grapes in half.
Mix together cranberries, grapes and cream.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until light and creamy.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Bake on 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on cookie sheets.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces and place in bowl.
Pour melted margarine over biscuits, tossing to coat.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over pieces, gently mixing until just coated.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and invert on plate.

title: texas beer muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in hot greased muffin pan at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: miracle bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Melt butter in oven in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham crackers.
Pour milk evenly over crackers.
Add chips, nuts and coconut and press firmly into top of mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool before cutting into bars.

title: rain forest chip dip
directions: Mash a soft, ripe avocado in a small bowl.
Thoroughly mix in the lemon juice.
Chop the tomato and add to the mixture.
Blend in the onion, salt, chili powder and mayo.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with corn chips.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: momma lela's old fashioned butter roll
directions: Roll pieces of dough thin; cut into 4 squares.
Spread butter over each piece; sprinkle with approximately 1/4 cup each of sugar or until well covered.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; dot with lemon flavor.
Roll up and place into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam and the bottom covered with 1/2 cup water, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
After completion of rolls, dot with margarine and sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When browning, pour can of evaporated milk over rolls. Let cook for 10 minutes more.
(If appears dry, pour regular milk over rolls; remove from heat to make juicy.)

title: crab dip
directions: In small bowl, combine dressing, crab meat, onions, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: praline confection
directions: Line a jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) with whole graham crackers. Bring the butter and sugar to a rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. When bubbling has stopped, add the nuts. Spoon over graham crackers. Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes. Cool slightly. Cut in squares.

title: waldorf red cake or red velvet cake
directions: Combine cocoa mix and coloring and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and food coloring mix and beat well.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well. Combine soda and vinegar, then add to cake mixture.
Beat mixture well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 (9-inch) layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test.

title: chicken seashell salad
directions: Make one day in advance. There should be nearly twice as much chicken as there is everything else.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Add tortillas and fry until crispy.
Add tomatoes, garlic, onions, cumin and jalapenos.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add chicken stock and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be placed in blender and pureed or eaten as is.
Serve hot.
Great on a cold night.

title: puffed oven pancake
directions: Place butter in a 10 inch oven proof skillet.
Place in 400° oven for 3-5 minutes or until butter is melted.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, milk and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Immediately pour into hot skillet.
Bake about 25 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Meanwhile, prepare Apple-Raisin Sauce.
Sprinkle pancake with powdered sugar and cut into wedges.
Serve with sauce. Serves 6.

title: chili laredo dip
directions: Melt together in small crock-pot or saucepan.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In a small bowl combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture and mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in a glass ring mold or 2-quart microwave-proof casserole.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook in microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: no cholesterol orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oil and orange juice.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Add peel.
In small bowl beat egg whites on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into flour mixture.
Turn into pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until cake springs back when slightly touched.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool completely on rack.
One loaf contains about 160 calories per 1/2-inch slice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add soup and milk. Simmer about 3 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Add broccoli, rice and water chestnuts.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: patricia liston's crumb cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and 1 stick butter; add eggs, one at a time. Add sour cream.
Sift 2 cups flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Mix 1/2 cup flour, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 stick butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: jello layer mold
directions: Grease 9x13 glass dish. Add 1 cup boiling water to one jello pkg. Stir. Then add 1/2 cup cold water. Chill until set.

Boil 2 cups milk to scalding, add sugar and mix until dissolved. Dissolve 2 envelopes gelatin into 1/2 cup cold water. Add to milk and sugar mixture. Add 2 Tbsp. vanilla to sour cream. Combine milk mixture and sour cream mixture.
Beat well. Spread 1 and 1/2 cups over the 1st chilled layer of jello. Let set.

Repeat with another layer of Jello and then a layer of sour cream mixture. The sour cream mixture may need to be slightly warmed each time because it gells as it sets. But be careful of pouring it when it's warm and pour each layer very carefully so as not to tear the layer beneath. When pieces are cut and served, they look stunning with alternating layers of color and white. Use two layers of red and two of green at Christmas. Or use green, orange, lemon, and cherry.

title: shrimp salad mold
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Melt cream cheese into soup.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Pour into soup mixture and cool.
Add other ingredients and pour into mold.
Garnish with olives, as desired. Chill overnight.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Mix shrimp and sauce.
Heat and serve.
Serve with Old London melba toast rye, if desired.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and in a nice size pot, place butter in pot.
Pour in potatoes and the listed ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat.
Check it occasionally and stir it.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: sweet meats
directions: Pour 1 envelope onion soup over meat; add preserves, then dressing.
Mix well on meat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in an aluminum foil covered pan, then uncover for 30 minutes or 1 hour until meat has browned.
Baste with juice from meat.

title: pickled garden relish
directions: Combine all in large skillet.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes.
Cool then refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Drain well to serve.
Keep rest refrigerated in covered container.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven, cook the beef, 2 cups onion and garlic until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients except fettuccine, beans and cheese. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Skim off fat.
Cook fettuccine; drain.
Keep warm.
In 2-quart saucepan, heat kidney beans; drain and keep warm.
Divide fettuccine into 8 servings.
Top with meat sauce, beans, remaining onions and cheese.

title: chocolate molded dessert
directions: Pour water over jello.
When thick enough, whip several minutes with electric mixer.
Fold pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts into jello mix.
Save out 1/2 cup wafers to put on top.
Pat a layer of crushed wafers on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread jello mixture over this and sprinkle with reserved wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Rinse in cold water 4 or 5 times.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add the squash mixture and return to a boil.
Pour mixture into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: morning in the vineyard fruit soup
directions: Peel and core apples, remove skins and seeds from cantaloupes. Mix first 5 ingredients in blender or food processor. Refrigerator until well chilled. Just before serving add Crackling Ros. Pour into stemmed glasses. Garnish with a cluster of white grapes. Serves 12.

title: strawberry or peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch.
Stir and cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from the stove and add the Jell-O and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Fill baked pie shells with strawberries or sliced peaches and pour mixture over them. Chill until set.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: lynn's ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, eggs, mayo and cheese.
Arrange broccoli on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with ham.
Spread soup mixture over top ham layer.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: dessert fruit salad
directions: Take juice of all fruit and mix with instant pie and pudding mix until thickened.
Mix all fruit when ready to serve.
Add bananas.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; cut up and mix with mayonnaise, soup, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over top of mixture.
Melt margarine in pan.
Mix in cornbread dressing and sprinkle over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Put into crusts and chill.

title: easy banana cake
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Mix corn meal, Bisquick and seasonings.
Add egg and enough beer so the batter just runs off a dipped fish.
Deep fry 2 fish at a time in a fry pan at 360°.
The fish are done when golden brown, about 3 1/2 to 5 minutes.

title: grilled turkey cutlets(a simple low-fat meal)
directions: Blanch cutlets in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Remove from water and pat dry.
Mix remaining ingredients and rub well into cutlets.
Grill 6 inches from heat 5 to 6 minutes each side until cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana walnut cake(sugar-free)
directions: In bowl, mix bananas with butter.
Add eggs; blend well.
Stir in flour; beat until smooth.
Add nuts and raisins.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Bring to boil the syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar; let come back to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add pecans; boil for 4 or 5 minutes, until lightly browned.
Take off heat.
Stir in soda.
Spread onto buttered tinfoil.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup together; spread over chicken.
Top with prepared stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo. Beat the eggs and add. Blend well. Sift the flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture. Add the bananas and walnuts (optional). Mix well. Put in 2 bread tins or one 8 x 8-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fried fish seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients in a plastic bag; shake well to mix.
Put in fish pieces and shake to coat.
Drop fish in hot oil to cook for 3 minutes or until light brown on all sides.
Fry Daddy fryer is great for this.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except dressing and Fritos. Add dressing about
30 minutes before serving.	Add corn chips just before serving.
Toss well to mix.

title: no bake chocolate dream cookies
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Blend well.
Stir in oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: chinese roast pork(bok choy)
directions: Roast a 2 pound fresh pork butt at 325° for 1 hour.
Baste with a mixture of 2 tablespoons each of honey, soy sauce, sherry, and the garlic and red food coloring.

title: summer spritzers
directions: Combine and serve well chilled over large glass of ice. Decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: raspberry cheese mold
directions: Combine cheese, pecans and onions.
Add mayonnaise; mix well. Place in a 4-cup mold; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Unmold onto a lettuce lined serving platter.
Pour raspberry jam over mold, or press an indention in center of mold and fill to overflowing with jam.
Serve with crackers.

title: first prize chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly dust with flour two 8-inch square cake pans.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Cook 3 minutes over low heat.
Wash, drain and chop broccoli.
Saute onion in remaining butter.
Stir in broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in broth; heat to simmering.
Add butter-flour mixture, mixing until smooth.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in warmed cream and serve.
(Add 5 slices American cheese for Broccoli-Cheese Soup.)

title: sand tarts(real old german style)
directions: Cream the butter until softened.

Add the 2 1/2 cups sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy. Add the beaten eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition. Add the flour in fourths, mixing until blended after each addition. Chill dough overnight.

title: custard frosting (the best)(frosts a 2 layer cake)
directions: Cook milk and flour on medium heat.
Cool until very cold.

title: easy chicken and onion bake
directions: Thaw package of frozen onions.
Place chicken in baking dish. In mixing bowl stir together all ingredients except paprika.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle finished casserole with paprika. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: frozen small onions with cream cubes

title: ravishing russian dip
directions: Scoop out inside of bread and use for "dippers".
Mix all ingredients together and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream together crisco, butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add extracts and milk; blend.
Mix in salt and flour.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or bundt pan.
Bake for 2 hours.
Do not open the oven during baking time.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Mix together soup, cheeses, butter and onion.
Layer potatoes and cheese mixture, then bake at 350°
until bubbly hot.

title: ronald reagan monkey bread
directions: Layer half of biscuits into Bundt pan.
In another pan bring butter, brown sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Add 1/2 liquid to biscuits in pan, then add the other 1/2 biscuits and add the rest of the liquid.
You can sprinkle with chopped nuts (both layers). Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool before removing from pan.
This can be pinched off in bite size.

title: quick and easy tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in saucepan for 8 to 10 minutes.
Make cheese mix with 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup milk.
Drain tuna fish.
Melt extra cheese with cheese mixture.
Add tuna fish.
Drain cooked macaroni; add to cheese and tuna mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: country fare turkey
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine hot water, milk and butter. Bring just to a boil.
Add pasta, contents of seasoning package, turkey or chicken, basil and green onions.
Reduce heat to medium, boil uncovered and stirring often for 5 to 7 minutes.
Pasta will be saucy, but will thicken upon standing.

title: texas bacon snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients except for bacon and crackers.
Cut bacon into 2-inch pieces.
Dip into the mixture and then roll in cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples; chop and set aside.
Pour oil in large mixing bowl; add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add to cream mixture; add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° in 10-inch tube or oblong pan 1 hour or until done.
Slightly grease pan.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix ingredients, then add 1 cup oil.

title: hot cranberry drink
directions: Mix all together and simmer until hot.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter together.
Beat egg well and add sugar and mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Add egg mixture to peanut butter and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Press in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan or dish.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix in separate bowl.
To assemble:
Spread bean dip in platter.
Top with avocado mix.
Layer sour cream mix.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: short'nin' bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add butter.
Place on floured surface and pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes and bake in moderate oven at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Heat syrup and sugar.
Cook until this comes to a hard boil. Remove and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.

title: stuffed potato soup
directions: Brown bacon in Dutch oven.
Remove from pot and throw away drippings.
Put potatoes and green onions in clean Dutch oven. Cover with water and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When potatoes are cooked, add 1 can Pet milk, Velveeta cheese (cubed) and crumbled bacon.
For a thicker soup, add instant potato flakes or cornstarch.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Cook 1 hour at low heat.
Can.

title: guacamole cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Sift together in a large bowl flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar.
Cut in buttermilk until bits are the size of medium peas.
Mix in milk only until ingredients are blended.
Do not overmix.
Form into a ball.
Pat out on floured board to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits using 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet or in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 10 biscuits.

title: delicious pork and beans
directions: Cut up one slice of uncooked bacon.
Fry remaining 4 slices until crisp.
Combine all ingredients into an ovenproof casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: polish sausage and cabbage
directions: Heat sausage in oil.
Add cabbage, corn, garlic, bouillon and water.
Steam until cabbage is done.

title: fruit garnishes for drinks
directions: Place a choice of fruit in ice cube tray.
Fill with water and freeze.
Pop out; use when needed to trim a drink.

title: surprise zucchini brownies(low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder and baking powder; set aside.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Reserve broth. In a saucepan, mix broth and soup and bring to a boil.
In a bowl, combine margarine, pepper, flour and buttermilk.
Pour broth over chicken in 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon batter evenly on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, until crust is browned.

title: best cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage, leeks, carrots, celery and garlic in margarine until vegetables are tender.
Add water and Herb Ox and simmer.

title: her slaw
directions: Mix together
all
ingredients	except oil.
Toss well. Add oil last; this is the secret of the recipe.
By adding the oil separately, it helps the slaw retain its flavor.

title: thanksgiving rolls
directions: Have ready 1 cup mashed potatoes. Mix together warm water, sugar and salt. Mix yeast with this mixture. Add eggs and shortening; mix well. Add potatoes and mix well. Mix in flour and put in the refrigerator in a large container. Roll out on floured board and cut. Let rise about 3 hours. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break up angel food cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, milk, sour cream and Cool Whip together.
Pour over top of cake; do not stir.
Pour frozen strawberries that have been added to glaze with sugar over top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice and cut in half onion.
Slice zucchini and saute with onion in butter until onion is soft.
Spread over casserole pan evenly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese evenly.
Brown and drain ground beef; add salt, pepper, flour and catsup.
Spread meat mixture over zucchini and cheese evenly.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover, sprinkle with additional 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is slightly browned.

title: summer macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box and cool.
Add carrots, tomatoes, cucumber, salt and pepper.
Mix all together with mayonnaise and chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch square pan. Put apples in pan. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creole pork chops(for microwave)
directions: This is an authentic washday receipt in it's original spelling, as it was written out for a bride four generations ago. 1 pile work britches and rags. bilin water. but don't bil - just rench and starch. then rench, blew and starch. of tee and set and rest and rock a spell and cout blessins.

title: cantaloupe and orange jam
directions: Pare cantaloupe and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Measure out the 5 cups.
Combine cantaloupe, sliced oranges, lemon juice and salt in 3-quart saucepan.
Boil vigorously for 15 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon and orange flavorings.
Boil rapidly until jam is thick and clear, stirring frequently with wooden spoon to prevent burning.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook meat in oil until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes for round steak, 10 to 15 minutes for sirloin. Add green peppers during last 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add canned tomatoes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until tomatoes are heated.
Serve over rice.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in egg, milk and oil. Heat #5 iron skillet on top of stove with 2 tablespoons oil in it. When skillet is hot, quickly pour in batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
When done, dump immediately on plate.

title: easy pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta per directions.
In large bowl combine pasta, sausage, pasta sauce and 2 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover, sprinkle with remaining 2 cups cheese and parsley and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 12.

title: chili
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil and brown the beef in it over medium high heat, crumbling beef with a fork until pink color disappears.
Set aside.
Puree onion soup in a blender and pour over beef, stirring over medium heat until it has the consistency of rice, breaking it up with fork as it heats.
Stir in spices. Add undrained beans, tomato paste and sauce, stirring until well combined.
Heat over low heat at least 20 minutes until piping hot and the flavors have blended.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add onion, then milk and beaten egg.
Drop by spoonful into pan or kettle, where hush puppies are fried to a golden brown or done in hot grease.

title: bean rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, refried beans and cheese.
Roll out biscuits (for a thicker bean roll put two biscuits together).
Put a dab of bean/meat mixture on biscuit and fold biscuit over mixture.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter baking dish. Slice potatoes. Layer in dish. In medium saucepan, melt butter; put in flour to make thick paste. Pour milk in all at once. Stir constantly until thick. Add cheese, salt and pepper. Keep stirring until melted. Pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° with lid on for 1 hour, then take lid off. Bake 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given, except nuts and egg whites.
Beat well.
Add nuts and fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased, floured tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand the pineapple, pineapple juice, baking soda, nuts, eggs, flour, vanilla and sugar.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mary's rice
directions: Mix all together and bake covered in large roaster for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
9 cups of rice.
Serves 20.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potatoes and packet of sauce mix into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling; stir in potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Stir just until blended; fill 12 greased muffin cups 1/2 full.
Add preserves or jelly to 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Brown the onions.
Remove from pan and brown meatballs. Drain.
Simmer sauce for 1 1/2 hours or longer, until it thickens.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Set aside. Grind up cookies in food processor or blender.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
You will need a 7-inch flower pot with no holes.
If it has holes, place Cool Whip lid in bottom of pot.
Alternate layers of cookies and cream cheese mixture.
Start with cookies; end with cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix butter and stuffing mix together.
Cook zucchini in boiling water for about 2 to 3 minutes and drain.
Toss 1/2 stuffing mixture, zucchini and other ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until bubbly in a 350° oven.

title: penny-pinching pot
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Add celery and garlic and saute for 5 minutes.
Combine onion soup and water.
Add tomatoies reserve tomato liquid and onion soup mixture to celery.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and cook 10 minutes.

title: bubbly fish bake
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, 1 1/2 cups of the cheese, macaroni and tuna.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbling.

title: fish balls souffle(fiske bollegrateng)
directions: Cut fish balls in small cubes.
Melt butter in pan; add flour, stirring well, then add milk to make sauce.
Fold in egg yolks. Cool.
Then fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden on top. Serve at once.
Chopped green onion and shrimp may be added.

title: hamburger soup
directions: After browning hamburger, add all ingredients and hamburger in a soup pot.
Add 6 cups of water and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: fruit punch bars and glaze
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Beat eggs and sugar at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze while hot.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop.
Marinate caps 1 hour in soy sauce.
Combine stems with remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Drain mushroom caps.
Stuff caps with meat mixture.
Brush tops with soy sauce.
Broil for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage with peppers and onions
directions: Slice onion into rings and green pepper into thin slices. Cook sausage on low flame for about 30 minutes. Add onions, green pepper, salt, pepper and oregano until vegetables are soft.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Add powdered sugar.
Then add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put pinch of salt in egg whites before beating.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Over medium heat in a medium frying pan, melt the butter.
Add the parsley and onions and saute until the onions are tender.
Add the lemon juice and garlic; stir and continue to saute about another 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and salt and stir to mix well. Saute until the shrimp are opaque and turn pinkish, about 5 minutes.
Do not overcook!
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, spinach, carrot, Egg Beaters, onion and Italian seasoning.
Set aside.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole bowl; bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil until both sides are browned. Drain fat. Stir in soup, water and pepper. Heat to boiling. Add broccoli. Reduce heat and simmer until broccoli and chicken are tender.

title: chocolate kiss pretzels
directions: Line cookie sheet with pretzels. Set Hershey's Kiss on top of each pretzel. Bake at 200° in oven for 3 to 5 minutes, until Kiss is soft enough to put M&M on top of. Cool in freezer 1 to 2 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In pan, mix sugar, milk and butter.
Bring ingredients to a boil.
Boil until forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat with spoon until creamy and smooth.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: camper's cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in sealed container.
Put 3 1/2 teaspoons of cocoa mixture in 1 cup hot water.
Stir.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion in skillet, stirring until beef is crumbly; drain. Reserve some of the olives for topping.

Layer refried beans, beef mixture, remaining olives, green chilies and cheese in greased 2-quart baking dish. Spread with taco sauce. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Spread with sour cream; sprinkle with green onions and reserve olives. Serve with nacho chips. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in a saucepan with 1/4 cup butter.
Heat over medium heat until melted and smooth, stirring often.
Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over and mix well.
Melt remaining butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve hot.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves six.

title: easy pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup cream of coconut, 1/2 cup rum, oil and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube cake pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool; remove from pan.
Poke holes 1-inch apart almost to bottom.
Combine cream of coconut and rum.
Pour over cake and chill thoroughly.
Garnish with Cool Whip, pineapple chunks, cherries and coconut.
Store in fridge.

title: baklava
directions: Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Brush baking tray (12 x 17-inch) with melted butter.
Place 15 fillo leaves at bottom brushing each with butter.
Spread one-third of walnut mixture on leaves.
Place 5 to 6 buttered leaves on mixture and spread additional third of walnut mixture.
Repeat with 5 to 6 leaves and mixture.
There must be 15 to 17 leaves to place on top layer. Brush top layer with remaining butter.
Score top sheets in diamond square shapes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool and pour warm syrup evenly over baklava.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Put water in a pot large enough to hold shrimp and all the seasonings.
Place it on a hot fire.
Drop the lemons, onions, garlic and celery into the water.
Add bay leaves and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salt until fluid is too salty for your taste.
Bring to a boil and then add the shrimp.

title: inga's hot potato salad
directions: In pot, cook chopped potatoes, carrots and celery.
Boil eggs. While all are still hot, combine with other ingredients.
Mix oil, vinegar and mayonnaise; stir all ingredients together.
Serve hot.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Mix the preceding ingredients and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken 'n broccoli
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish.
Prepare broccoli per box instructions.
Place broccoli in bottom of dish.
Cream the soup with mayonnaise.
Boil chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Layer 1/2 of the soup mixture over broccoli.
Place chicken on soup mixture. Cover chicken with remaining soup mixture. Top with grated cheese, Italian bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molded apple salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water, then dissolve in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Stir in next 3 ingredients and pour 1/4 cup into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Add about 1/4 cup apples and chill until firm. Chill rest of gelatin until thickened, but not firm.
Mix remaining apples and next 4 ingredients together.
Whip the cream and fold in.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and chill several hours.
Unmold on lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Make
filling first by combining and cooking down until thick (like
preserves)
dates,
1 cup sugar and 1 cup water. Stir in one cup chopped pecans when mixture is cooled.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Boil beef until tender; break into stringy bits.
Combine beef and hamburger.
Add other ingredients; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour over slow heat.
This lets the flavor become savory.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: half moons
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients; beat well.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll on floured board; cut to desired size.
Bake at 375° on lower oven rack for 5 minutes, then on upper rack for 5 minutes.
(This step is very important!)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew the frying chicken.
Combine meat from 1 medium chicken or 3 cups leftover chicken or turkey, the sour cream and soup. Place in greased casserole.
Top with stuffing mix into which you have tossed the melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and salt together.
Add the egg yolks and vanilla and mix well.
Add the flour to the wet mixture and mix well.
Place by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press your thumb into the center of each cookie and fill the well left with jam or jelly.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas, and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate and slice right before serving.

title: goo goo bars
directions: Melt over low heat the first 3 ingredients; let cool.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Refrigerate until hard.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, except corn.
Add the cream-style corn.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until set.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a large bowl.
When the pudding begins to thicken, add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
In the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of graham crackers.
On top of the crackers, put 1/2 of the pudding mixture, another layer of graham crackers, the rest of the pudding and a third layer of graham crackers.
In a smaller bowl, combine the chocolate icing and 2 tablespoons of milk.
Mix well and spread the icing on the third layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: midget pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with 1 tablespoon flour; place in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Mix 1 cup water, broth, soup mix, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick applesauce rolls
directions: Melt
butter in 9-inch round cake pan.
Add applesauce, cinnamon,
raisins
and brown sugar; blend.
Top with biscuits and bake
in
oven for 15 minutes.
Place serving plate over pan and turn upside down.
Sauce should be on top.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 rolls.
